tions where things can get nasty require you to pay some attentions in order to beat it, or you can just sit back, relax, enjoy the show.If you are available to play co-op, co-op is not too different from single player, which just add some additional chaos on your screen. The soundtrack in RoR is another feature to enjoy, musics in the background certainly polish the game into a another level it is simply astonishing and perfect. You can find all the little details proving that there are people (devs) who care about their games, and it is tons of fun when you are relaxing and reading some introductions of the item you've been using in the game, as well as the monster logs. Sometimes the game can crash if data overloaded (because it's the nature of the game), or some minority bugs happen to get in your way but overall RoR is a must-have game, and trust me you need to go deeper to witness the sorrow of the rain.--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Update: 2016/11/24It has been years when this game released. I really hope for a series or a huge update, from the bottom of my heart I wish these devs don't cool down this game. At last I hope RoR can get a reward."
