,Recommended,248820,8403029,"Posted: 29 December, 2013",all,Moobeat,"I highly recommend Risk of Rain - very fun roguelike featuring several classes with four abilities each, difficult scaling up based on time played per run ( do I collect loot and make next level harder or rush to keep the last level easier ) , up to four player co op, wonderful art style, and killer sound track. My only note of warning is that it takes a little getting used to on the keyboard vs a game pad.To expand a bit on the class options, here are three examples:Commando: First class everyone has access to, others are unlocked as you play and progress, find them in levels, or unlock achievements. Basic attack is a ""double tap"" shot with his pistol and other abilities are: piercing knock back burst of bullets, a roll that lets you escape / pass through enemies quicikly, and his ""ultimate "" ( longer cd then rest ) ability is a rapid fire of abilites that stun nearby enemies.Enforcer: Very stocky character. His basic attack is a short range shot gun blast then he also has a shield slam that knocks enemies back, a defensive stance that blocks all damage from a certain direction, and his ultimate type ability is a stun grenade.Bandit: Basic attack is a normal rifle blast. Has a dynamite toss ability that does aoe damage, a smoke bomb that stealths him and stuns when he comes out of stealth, and his ultimate is a big headshot that does oodles of damage and resets his other abilities if it kills an enemy.It's a really fun system to me rather than Rogue Legacy where your abilities are like magic and auto attack. Some of the other classes include a sniper, engineer fellow with turrets and missiles, an acid beast, and more!"
