,Recommended,248820,25700076,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,Yevgenos,"Risk of Rain is a 2d platform rogue-like shooter with an increasing difficulty level that goes up according to time spent while playing: the longer your session - the harder it gets.Prepare to die.A lot.The game is not as easy as one might expect.Right off the bat you are put in a situation where a space cargo ship, UES Contact Light, in which you happen to be in, crashes on a hostile planet.You have 12 characters, all of which require you to do specific objectives ingame (beat the game on the hardest difficulty level, kill 3 specific bosses, obtain specific item combination.)Each character packs a four pack of abilities (So you will find the one that suits you)At the begining you have your first, already unlocked character - The Commando(My favourite of the whole shebang).A very versatile character that can handle most situations flawlessly.While playing, you collect items, scattered through chests that fell off the ship and shrines, that can require either your health or your money.Every item is a unique game changer. One can place fungus that heals you if you stand still for a few seconds, one amplifies your shots with bonus explosive damage, one can stop time when your health goes to a critical level and one item even gives you a second chance in case you die.The more items you get, the more powerful you become, and if you stack up items ( get more and more of the same one) the effect and amplification level increases (although some items have a limit on how many times the effect will improve).At the end of the game, each character has a different outcome. (They are really spine-chillin if you think of em afterwards) Here's the one of the Commando:""...and so he left, witheverythingbut his humanity.""The game also has multiplayer (online and locally).It can be a pain in the a$$ to get it working (it requires hamachi or tungle to work) but once you do, it is a whole lot more fun to beat the game with friends and die together :)P.SThere are artifacts, hidden throughout some levels, that change the game completely.One can give you the ability to choose a specific item of your choice instead of getting a random one, one will spawn a specific boss every 10 minutes and one will spawn only one random enemy type per stage. Great for making the game more customizable and can help you unlock characters. (But don't overuse them or the game loses the fun behind it)Overall Scores:Gameplay- 10/10Story - 8/10 (requires you to collect monster logs and even then it is mosly lore since characters do not speak here)Replayability - 10/10Multiplayer (once set) - 9/10Final Verdict:9/10TLDR:2d rogue like dark souls in space."
