,Recommended,248820,7900191,"Posted: 3 December, 2013",all,Zencodion,"Risk of Rain is a Indie/Platformer with rogue-like elements. In Risk of Rain you fight through hordes of Enemies that spawn on the level your in and they keep spawning more over time as you try to go through the level, collecting items, killing the Enemie waves, and trying to find the teleporter/exit. You get Gold and Exp. through killing the Enemies that you can use to unlock chests or pray to shrines to get access to items that help you through the game. When you get to the teleporter you have to fight through a 90 sec. spawning wave while trying to kill the boss of that level. The game gets harder the longer you play. It starts off very easy and it can go to the hahaha difficulty if you survive a long enough time. The point of Risk of Rain is to survive as long as you can while trying to get a lot of items that can help you throughout the game and to help you kill the final boss....if you can survive that long that is...Mwahahahah."
