que, you can also hold all of the items you find through the game!There are also ""Use items"" that serve like a 5th skill, you can only hold one and i find it hard to choose which one is coming with me, mostly the ones that the bosses drop because they are the strongest and help alot.How does it play: As the trailer says, the game gets harder as you play, it gets harder with the difficulty you choose and its already hard by default. This game is a real challenge, but the challenge is what makes it fun. While you play the game the game count for how many time you have been playing it, it will be filling a bar at the top right corner of the screen and it can get pretty stressful, you always get scared of exploring the world because you will be losing time and fears that the game is getting harder, its like someone is following you.Apparentally the game has many different levels for the stages, there is a variation of teleporter locations and levels that you will get, the map may never be the same.tl;dr: you a patient and skillful player? get it, you new to video games and not patient? dont get itvery funny thanks guysi will be playing this gamerightnow"
,Recommended,248820,15993204,"Posted: 24 May, 2015",all,[Cash.net] Xgpmcnp,"After 150 hours of playtime and writing the Handbooks to Every Survivalists, I think I've played enough to write a review on this.What I enjoyed from Risk of Rain:-The graphics are really nice, tiny pixels but lots and lots of details!-The soundtrack is divine, really helps for immersion-The ""Time=Difficulty"" feature is great, requiring the player to manage his time correctly or else die-The amount of items is gigantic, making every run unique (Unless you've got Command..)-Talking about Command, the artifacts change the whole game and makes you play very differently-10 different characters that all plays completely differently-The game is hard. At least at first, as I don't feel challenged at all anymore, even in Monsoon (Sadly!)What I didn't like:-The Multiplayer doesn't work very well, extremely prone to crashes mid-game and unable to join back-As much as I love the artifacts, you'll only ever use 3 of them after a while (Glass, Command and Sacrifice mostly.)What I think this game needs:-A randomize button. Press it, and it chooses you a character and artifacts randomly! Since every Artifact and every Character radically change the way you'll play, that'd make Risk of Rain a game where you truly need to adapt to what you have and surely increase the playtime I have on it of another 20 hours minimum.-Less lag on multiplayer. I am unable to do runs of over 40 mins because of crashes on my friends' PCs, and if they fixed just the crashes I would play this forever.-Nerfing Command would be a good idea, because at this point it completely kills the RDM of the game. Maybe make it you can choose but you get a LOT less items on the run, so you get those you want but not as much?It's sad they don't update this game anymore, because it isn't optimized correctly, at least for multiplayer. One of the last updates greatly reduced lag on the Risk of Rain level which I am extremely grateful for, but crashes on Multiplayer kills the online fun..Still, even though I said some bad of this game, it remains an extremely good single player game with tons of replayability (140 of those hours were on solo..) and it is able to make you change your playstyle really often. Get this if you're a fan of any hard game!"
