,Recommended,248820,14523075,"Posted: 17 February, 2015",all,Pakkidis,"9/10Overview: 2d Rogue-Action/PlatformerThe Good:+10 characters each with their own unique attack and abilities.+Randomized levels every time you start a new game.+Over 100 items ensuring lots of variety+Plenty of things to unlock. You first start out with only one character: the commando and a handful of items. As you play and complete challenges, you unlock more characters and items making it easier to get to the end of the game.+Every good rogue game I've played has a nice sense of pacing. What seems like an impossible task in the beginning slowly becomes easier once you start understanding the mechanics. Making it to the last boss is a very satisfying feeling.+ One of the main premises of the game is that as time goes on, the harder enemies become. This creates somewhat of an interesting balance to the game. Normally you may think that you should just complete each level as fast as possible however this may leave you underpowered in the next level. Take too long in a level and you may find the enemies too hard to defeat. Finding the right balance between killing enemies, collecting as many items in a level and staying above the difficulty curve is part of the strategy.+ I love the music. Fantastic soundtrack.The Average:Although there are 10 character to choose from, some of them are not that good compared to others and some were designed with multiplayer in mind.Online multiplayer community is deadConclusionThis is one of my favorite rogue games on steam. It has an addicting quality to it. Playing each character, getting rare items and having a good run is one of the hallmarks of a great rogue game."
