76561197992886766,Recommended,248820,7708207,"Posted: 21 November, 2013",all,Honorable_D,"Wow, this is quite the little gem. A very, VERY hard little gem, though!Imagine Contra combined with Binding of Isaac and some Rogue Legacy and you'll have a basic gist of what this game is about.You start the game with just 1 class but as you do special events and just plain find the new classes hidden in the levels you'll unlock more. Each class has 4 unique abilites with different lengths on their cooldowns though most classes have 1 spammable ""basic"" attack with no cooldown.  Examples of some abilites are the Commando's Suppression Fire that has a 5 sec cooldown but blasts for huge dmg and stuns enemies and then there is the Engineer's Thermal Harpoons that fires 4 heating-seeking missiles for great damage! The classes really are cleverly designed and balanced and they offer a sometimes totally different play style.And then we have the loot.Oh yes, like Binding of Isaac there are many unlocks you can have fun getting plus just tons of items from the get-go. Items are crazy such as a shoulder mounted missile launcher, a cursed mask that turns killed enemies into ghosts that help you, at least 6 different kinds of drones that follow you and auto-attack enemies, magic mushrooms that sprout up and heal you super fast if you stand still for a few seconds, a tesla coil that chain zaps many enemies that get near you... I could go on and on.This game also has multiplayer co-op if thats your thing though you do have to fiddle with port forwarding or Himachi.All in all its a great lil game for only 10 bucks if you love action roguelikes/platformers!"
