76561197966674539,Recommended,248820,9413981,"Posted: 10 March, 2014",all,Mikeronomicon,"Risk of Rain is a fun, incredibly difficult rogue-like. It opens with you crash-landing on an alien planet and the goal is to survive long enough to get back to your ship. Along the way you will encounter mobs that get more difficult with time, and plenty of items. The items are worth mentioning because you unlock the bulk of them by completing challenges through the game, and they can really make or break a run. This is also a downside, as sometimes you get a bunch of healing items, but I've never played a game where I felt like I was doing enough damage, and by 45 minutes into the game weak enemies will have 2000 - 5000 hp, but you are still doing 100 - 200 points of damage. The randomness of the items does make it fun, and some runs you will get a ton of helpful/awesome items. I have yet to tire of this game, having played for nearly 100 hours. The art is fantasticly done, the music is good, and the classes feel different and varied enough. I only have 2 complaints: The aformentioned item snafu mentioned previously, (seriously, sometimes the items you get in the first stage are so useless that you'll have trouble making past the first boss) and the lack of full controller support. Having to use the mouse to select things, including my character isn't a make or break for me, but it is unfortunate.I never tried the multiplayer, so I don't know if it is good or not, but the single player is a lot of fun and pretty addictive, especially if you don't mind playing for an hour only to die and have to start over. I highly recommend this game to anyone who enjoys a challenge."
