76561198034600665,Recommended,248820,10095608,"Posted: 12 May, 2014",all,Sabrebear,"This is a game you should play. It's an action roguelike, and every playthrough is short, which might turn some people off. However, the mechanics are geared towards this setup. The pacing of the game works nicely, sitting in the nice groove that MOBA style games lie, where games are long enough to be engaging, but short enough to be quickly replayable.Difficulty increases as the time runs up, and metroid-style exploration in the game's levels next to that adds pressure to the time. Should you explore the level with the money you've received by beating the boss and his minions, or hurry to the next level to make sure the game stays at a good difficulty level? Should you stick around and grind, or push for the final boss as fast as you can? These quick decisions make the game engaging, along with the Artifacts system, well-balanced difficulty settings, and co-op play to add to the replay value.The item list is also impressive, with one of the artifacts allowing for the fun of min-maxing your character, and the default setting making most items random, adding to the spontaneity of the game. Items can be unlocked with challenges that test your knowledge of the character's skills, or put you in interesting scenarios. For instance, one of the Commando's (the initial character) challenges involve using his tactical rolls to evade fatal blows, which helps ingrain skill with the character.The only gripe I have with the game is the rate at which new characters are unlocked. Many characters must be unlocked through hidden events on the map, which are difficult to find without guidance. While this approach is fine for Artifacts, which are supposed to be hard to find, some characters are ridiculous, like the Robot Janitor HAND-E's hiding spot-- which is hard to find except by accident.Overall, I would thoroughly reccomend Risk of Rain. Go buy it!"
,Recommended,248820,10068208,"Posted: 9 May, 2014",all,Slippery Fat Man,Amazing game and I reccommend it to anyone who is interested in rogue-lites. It is very fun and the different classes combined with different items give each character their own depth. No one playthrough is the same and all of them have different experiences to get to the end. It's tough as nails at times but very satisfying to play. With the introduction of the new artifacts it gives an entirely new feel to the game. Different characters have different builds to do better with which is a lot of fun. This game still has many more hours for me and I keep wanting more. I am a little biased though. It is amazing and everyone should give it a try out. Easily worth your $10.
