,Recommended,248820,14486660,"Posted: 15 February, 2015",all,jd,"This is one of those games that you want to play for ten minutes and end up spending an afternoon on.It's a great game, with online/offline co-op, simple but engaging gameplay (each character has 4 buttons: a standard attack and three specials with cooldowns) and permadeath. It has some roguelike elements and a very good unlock system, implementing the old standard of 'I must collect all the things' with the added utility that the 'collectibles' are actually bonuses that work for your current run.The lore is interesting, the art is pretty, the gameplay is hard (or easy, depending on your luck in-run).While there are unlockable characters, they are not better than the starting character, but simply different. Each new character supplies a new way of playing the game and a total change of perspective.All in all, buy it. And if it's on sale, buy two."
