,Recommended,248820,15579581,"Posted: 27 April, 2015",all,an person,"This is one of the best games I've ever had the privilege to play. Sure, it can seem obtusely difficult at times, but when you mess up and die it's never the game's fault. You really feel like it's you that made the mistake. The exoctic alien planet you traverse throughout the game has been beautifully modeled with retro graphics, and the soundtrack is one that I would place very highly on a top 10. I would even go as far as to say It's even better than some other  popular roguelike platformers out there, such as Rogue Legacy and Spelunky. It could be that the gameplay is based more around combat, or that the difficulty increasing over time mechanic is unique to this game. You have to find a balance between slowing down to get money (or muney), tracking down items, and rushing to find the teleporter.  All of these make for an extremely polished and addictive experience, and the game doesn't take much processign power to deliver gameplay constantly at a silky-smooth 60 FPS. With several classes to unlock, artifacts to find, over 100 different items, and unlimited replayability due to random elements, this is probably the best 10 bucks you'll ever spend."
,Recommended,248820,9739821,"Posted: 5 April, 2014",all,"Jebus, Son Of Gode","I give this an 8 out of 10. The gameplay is challenging, and it keeps you deciding whether or not to be rushing to the next level in hopes of beating it faster, or exploring for as many items as possible beforehand.The multiplayer can only be played with by friends who share their IP with you. This is one of the two flaws with the game that I have noticed. But other than that, what can go wrong with cooperative play while trying to survive together? Multiplayer takes teamwork. You cannot just hog all the items and expect your partner to survive.The other flaw is how things work with item unlocks. They force you to either get them by going into the game and actually only trying to get said acheivement, or you just play normally and barely get any of them. The less items you have unlocked, the less likely you are to succeed at this game, so start farming those achievements!A strong game overall with few flaws, would definitely reccommend this for anyone who likes a challenge, pick this up if you have the money. You will not regret it."
