,Recommended,248820,7782702,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,"vermin ""verminium"" supreme","This is by far one of my most favorite games of the year. It's like an old school shoot-em up, like Contra, pushed to 11.There are currently 10 classes in the game, each with a different skillset, so you should find one you are comfortable with. The classes range from a sniper who can one-shot bosses under the right circumstances, a riot officer who can plant his shield on the ground to absorb all damage from the front but renders him immobile and an engineer who can plant turrets and mines. You unlock each class by doing various objectives like beating the game or doing a mini event.Each class has four different abilities. You start out with the Commando who is very very good and is one of the best in my opinion (but I like the Huntress more). His primary damaging ability (spammable) is dual shot which fires two shots for damage,  a railgun like ability that fires a straight shot piercing all enemies, a dodge roll that gives you invulnerability frames, and an ability that can fire in both directions for quite a bit of damage. The overall combat in the game is very satisfying and if you die you know it was your fault and not the games. The game also has native 360 pad support, which is what I use to play, not so sure on the ds3 pad support though.There is a selection of active items you can pick up that can do some pretty cool things like summon some backup drones or summon a shadow clone to mimic your abilities. There are also many passive items you can get that give you various bonuses like enemies drop meat cubes on death that heal you when you pick them up, every 4th basic attack will pierce and summon bolts after you kill an enemy that will seek out others and damage them.The difficulty in the game can range from easy to holy♥♥♥♥♥♥this is the worst thing in the world, it really all depends on the items you get in the game. You can get some insane items on the first stage that can carry you through the rest of the game, like Infusion which grants maximum health on each kill or 56 Leaf Clover which makes farming much easier as it makes elite mobs, ones that have a white border around their health bar, have a chance to drop items.The level variety is really nice as they include a snowy levels, lava levels, underwater levels (no drowning involved!), and a space ship. There is also a hidden level in the game, can you find it without looking it up? The levels in the game are procedurally generated meaning that there will never be a chest inside a wall or the teleporter to exit each stage isn't inaccessible.The soundtrack in the game is just amazing, that's all I can say. Go listen to it for yourself! My favorite track ishttp://youtu.be/iSnOWqTPUNQ. If you want throw your money at Chris Christodoulou for this amazing soundtrack athttp://chrischristodoulou.bandcamp.com/album/risk-of-rain.My closing words are BUY THIS GAME you will not be disappointed onebit.http://fc01.deviantart.net/fs70/f/2012/199/d/0/shut_up_and_take_my_money_by_lolikips-d34yx16.png"
,Recommended,248820,7742680,"Posted: 25 November, 2013",all,S+,"This is an incredibly fun 2d roguelike. Like other roguelikes, it is possible to be killed throughout the game because of a simple slip up, and there is a reliance on getting the proper items in order to succeed in later levels. It's very possible to die on the first level simply because you don't find any useful items.The emphasis on ""permanent death"" for a character may be offputting to some, but beating the entire game takes about an hour, and dying is not a tremendous setback. The fun comes from the gameplay itself, not the progression to the end.The game is definitely worth $10 based on the singleplayer alone, and I've put many more hours into this game than games with a considerably larger price tag, but if that is not enough for you it has up to four player co-op. The multiplayer is fun but expect to die a lot more often. Money and experience is split between players which can make progress difficult, as items are not shared.This game is a great example of the roguelike genre, and great value for an individual or group of friends."
,Recommended,248820,7750651,"Posted: 25 November, 2013",all,Door Master,"This game is actually rather addicitve, it took me while to buy it, because my brother was REALLY trying to convince me to buy it, and when I watched gameplay, I couldn't see the appeal, but I eventually caved in and bought it in the end.And to my surprise I really enjoyed it.The simplicity of the way the game plays, and the simple pixel art works wonders for the game, and the music definitely completes the atmosphere.I do have a couple of things to say though.1: The music isn't 'AS' great as everyone seems to be making it out, yes, it's pretty good, but I have heard much better, it's definietly not soundtrack of the year, but you will enjoy it, I can promise you that.2: The game can start to slow down later on in the game, especially when you get to the last 2-3 difficulties and it decides to spawn about 100 enemies at once which it can't handle, especially considering by that point it's also trying to calculate the damage to all of them, and whether to make the 100 enemies explode, set on fire, give you health, bleed, poison, slow, and a few more things, this can slow the computer down if you don't have a fast enough computer to handle all of that.3: THE MULTIPLAYER SHOULD COME WITH A WARNING.  Basically, you have to either port-forward or use Hamachi, both of which are a real pain in the backside if you don't know what you're doing, luckily I have previous experience with Hamachi from Terraria's bad multiplayer.Let me point out though, that whilst the multiplayer is a real pain to get going, once you de eventually get it going, it's probably one of the best multiplayer experiences I've had in a while, and it's definitely worth iall the blood, sweat and tears it took to get it working."
