,Recommended,248820,8317227,"Posted: 26 December, 2013",all,Saturnine Aberrance,"This game.My god.People play games like Binding of Isaac, and I can theoretically comprehend the enjoyment they derive from such games, but I myself have never been able to enjoy them. Risk of Rain, on the other hand, has some of the same elements like character unlocking and item unlocking and stuff, but this game makes it so wonderful on an entirely new level. I cannot praise this game enough. The game has a wonderful difficulty curve, where the more time you take the harder everything gets. Some people are under the impression that it stops at the highest displayed difficulty, but it keeps going.You may feel like a god at times, but if you take too long, no matter how strong you are, you will be smacked down if you become complacent. The difficulty is satisfying and fair, and the entire feel of how you approach fights and how you do things is SO strongly correlated by which character you are playing that you can't at all approach a situtation the same way with one character as you did as another: It's an extremely unique experience.There is an absolute ton of items in this game, all with interesting effects, and you unlock more by completing challenges with any character, or a specific one depending, and it all feels awesome.The art style is absolutely gorgeous. It's very 2d and in a lot of ways is somewhat low-res, your character for example is entirely made up of only a few pixels. But the few pixels used in any given element are used very well, and it looks amazing in the end. The backgrounds as well are absolutely incredible, the background in either of the first level possibilities and the final level in particular are absolutely incredible.The soundtrack: It's unfair. I feel very bad for every other developer in existence who now has to make soundtracks for their games now that this game's soundtrack is around. It's unbelievable how well this soundtrack fits the game. The music is amazing and I can't get enough of it, it's soooooooo good. Beyond even the music, the sound effects on attacks and enemies is excellent as well (with the minor exception of some spider enemies in the mid game who are a biiit too into making their sound) in that they impart a great feel for what is happening and the weight behind the attacks that you can rarely afford to let hit you.I could probably go on for days. This game is absolutely incredible and I love just about every bit of it. My only regret is that I didn't know about it while it was in Kickstarter, so I missed my opportunity to throw money at it in development. Anyone reading this shouldabsolutelyget this game, and even get copies for friends/encourage friends to get it as well so you can all play it in co-op and be completely amazed by how good this is."
