76561197979654196,Recommended,248820,8522132,"Posted: 2 January, 2014",all,Cache,game of the year 2013
,Recommended,248820,8159045,"Posted: 20 December, 2013",all,了此一生,"What is a strategy?By definition, a strategy is a plan of action or policy designed to achieve a major or overall aim. In this case, the overall aim is to get to the end of the game and beat the boss. Yet to have a plan, you need to know what you need to do. In the case of this game, the only things you know are the four skills that come with the character you pick.The game is a constant new experience every time you play it, no matter the difficulty. You could ace an excellent run, and die 12 minutes into your next run. This game focuses not on the story, and not on developing your character, but simply the experience. The item pool is huge- over a 100 items you could get that could come together and assist you in beating the game, or be completely useless. It all depends on your style of play.While the amount different levels you can get aren't too high, your starting location, item chests, shrines, and teleporters are all scattered about randomly each level to get a different experience despite it being a level that has been seen before.Another plus to the game is the multiplayer. It uses direct IP connection (like Terraria) so you can play with up to 10 friends or join a random group online. While a large amount of players can mean more firepower, monsters you fight become stronger and the overall amount of items you get doesn't change much- meaning to play as a team, you can't just pick up every item you get or keep every chest to yourself. You have to question yourself- ""Am I able to play efficiently with the items I have currently?"" ""Does anybody else on the team need items?"" ""Do I really need this item?"" Playing multiplayer focuses a major part on the teamwork aspect in the game.While there are upsides, there are downsides too.The biggest downside you will come to is the issue of lag. The game typically runs at 60 fps for everybody, and half that if you are recording. Once you get to high times and levels, the lag increases. The amount of monsters spawning at every second on and around your screen causes a lot of fps lag, and the graphics (while being pixelated) from attacks and item drops also boosts the lag you can get. In example, after 65 minutes of gameplay and 7 drones collectively firing at a large group of monsters, my game froze and crashed like the Titanic. I was upset because I just unlocked a new class and hadn't beaten the game as the class I was playing as. The lag is different for everybody though- it simply depends on how well your computer can handle it.All in all, I definitely recommend this game. It is well balanced and well thought out, and even finishes with a dramatic/feely quote that is different for each class you beat the game with. I applaud Chucklefish, the makers of this game."
