76561198040944606,Recommended,248820,7942316,"Posted: 6 December, 2013",all,Oddwood,"Risk of Rain is best described as a 2D action-roguelike-platformer. At it's core, players must proceed through random levels with different layouts in search of a teleporter. They must do this whilst fending off onslaughts of enemies, collecting items to live slightly longer and all with haste, as the difficulty amplifies depending on how long players have been, well, playing.Having crash-landed on an openly hostile alien planet, your job is to find your ship and get the hell off said planet. The local wildlife are highly unimpressed by your presence, and want to remove your face. And they will do so in droves.As players lurch deeper into the game, more items and characters will become available to them. For instance, take the Enforcer; a lumbering tank on legs carrying a shield and a shotgun. Yes, he's slow, but he certainly makes up for it with power.One of the more satisfying elements of this game is ironically when you meet your maker. Unlike most roguelike games, this game focuses on combat. This means that death is a matter of human error as opposed to shoddy game mechanics, luck and stats to determine a hit or miss. It feels rather satisfying, if you can overcome the game's steep learning curve.In short, Risk of Rain is an insanely difficult yet highly satisfying and overall fun game to play. The game also supports local and online co-op (which is rather rough but fun), so bring some friends along too if you want!"
