76561197986365521,Recommended,248820,9255659,"Posted: 25 February, 2014",all,Diarrhea Cactus,"If you ever want to relive the old NES days where game difficulty added to the fun this is the game to get.  Risk of Rain brings a refreshing and realistic difficulty factor.  The graphics on this game go to show, that not everything needs to be ""pretty"" to be considered a good game as gamers of the new generation would have you believe.  Risk of Rain provides you with multiple characters but only one starting character.  The game can be played single of coop with up to three other people which makes the game easier.  Risk of Rain was truly aimed at a single player experience but you won't last long if you don't have patience as the difficulty of the game increases the longer you play regardless of what initial difficulty you choose.  There are many lootable items that build your power, some may seem worthless while others more apparent in their use.  It is all about the drop and when it drops.  Choosing the wrong item when given a choice can make your life more miserable.  Bosses are challenging at first but become easier as you continue to play and learn the habits of the enemies and bosses.  Overall, this game has great replaybility and ten dollars is a fair price to pay for something that you don't see often anymore.... a well made game."
