,Recommended,248820,8625165,"Posted: 8 January, 2014",all,CombatSquid,"RoR is probably the most unforgiving action platformer I've ever played, and I love it. The game consists of you being stranded on different planets while plowing your way through hoardes of never ending aliens and monsters that would like nothing more than to tear you apart while you search for a teleporter to take you to the next level. You net EXP and 'muney' from each kill that you use to purchase items you'll find spawned randomly across the map, each one making you more and more powerful until your bottom screen is cluttered (in a ""I am your dark messiah overlord you can never hope to kill me lul"" kind of way) with them. Unlocking every character and weapon in the game is a hefty chore in itself and even though this game is great, I can't recommend buying it without a buddy system. The co-op is perfect with a friend to back you up, that will split item drops with you (pub games are known for free-for-all item hoarding which leaves everyone else screwed). So if you're into challenging, unforgiving, 'rougelike' killing action, give this a shot."
