,Recommended,248820,7907829,"Posted: 4 December, 2013",all,RipTlde,"Risk of Rain is an addicting and fun to play sort of beat-em up RPG which takes on some rouge-like qualities. The basic gameplay is killing seemingly randomly spawned enemies to acquire new items to become stronger and beat bosses until you progress to the final stage. This game has a story that while not the most prominent of features is still interesting in terms of lore. The items and monsters you come accross get catalogued and have individual descriptions which builds a somewhat deep world for the game to take place in. As you play the game more items and characters to play become unlocked. Unlockables are extremely motivating although some of them can be a bit difficult on normal mode and playing on easy mode is such a tremendous gap of difficulty that it sometimes makes the player feel cheated when choosing it. One of the reasons is that the separate difficulties directly effect the difficulty curve in the game. As you play the game automatically gets harder after set intervals. This is a unique and a well-done risk against reward mechanic, but I feel easy mode may make dilute it too much.Risk of Rain's main gameplay is quite rewarding. As the initial starting class you can roll out of enemy danger-zones and shoot from afar. Many of the unlocked characters have their own unique gameplay style which can become quite interesting during multiplayer. Though some of the characters feel marginally less fun to play than others. On occasion a player may find themselves with a slow first level because the enemy spawing is quite sparatic initially. This can often lead to poor chance at later progression automatically. At the end of each level there is a boss fight which can range from very difficult to downright child's play. Sometimes bosses will spawn on a platfrom that the player can shoot from but the boss can't attack from. The boss fights are almost always exciting though and the boss and enemy variety throughout the game is large enough to where traversing the levels is seldom boring.Overall, Risk of Rain is a fun game with rewarding gameplay. If you have friends to play the game gets even better. Some of the unlockables can be a bit tough, but easy mode will allow for smooth travels while unlocking new items and classes.Risk of Rain receives 5 large potatoes out of 7."
,Recommended,248820,9095720,"Posted: 13 February, 2014",all,Raeldon,"This game really stands out as a gem in my eyes. AMAZING music (reminds me a lot of MegaMan titles..early ones :) The gameplay is very smooth, although i sometimes have trouble grabbing onto ropes as i fly on by, but it may just be my logitech dualaction showing it's age.  There are no apparent flaws that I can see after a good day's worth of playing--in the gameplay and the style they're going for.  It seems perfectly fair and ESPECIALLY hard, but i'm glad its difficult because it really adds to the replayability.  I've unlocked about 30% of the game so far but i would say i'm playing a little above average so don't assume you'll get 100% in 3 days.  It just won't happen.  I know it won't for me anyway!  The flowing nature of the gameplay and scavenging aspect makes me feel like i'm playing something that was really well thought out and tested.  There are points where you do end up thinking 'how the hell am i going to pull this off' but more likely than not a few minutes later you'll be thinking WHOAAA I DID IT! All in all a very good title, i bought it on sale but after playing it for 7 hours i can recommend buying this game for the full price any day.  I haven't played coop yet but judging how the characters play out i can see how it would be a great time with friends!"
