,Recommended,248820,8812087,"Posted: 22 January, 2014",all,BORN TO DIE WORLD IS A FUCK,"A maddeningly addictive action shooter in the same vein as Binding of Isaac. Features similar item driven, shallow, twitch-based combat, but in this case the addition of multiple, actually varied classes helps significantly alleviate the lack of gameplay depth. Minute-to-minute gameplay is closer to Diablo, in that it focuses on constant movement, cooldown management, and enemy crowd control. Ability cooldowns are a frustrating band-aid solution for proper game balance. Movement and combat feel restricted; better mobility options and more/more interesting abilities would be welcome. Basically, the only problem with RoR is that it would be better with more time in the oven; this is pretty high praise actually, and indicative of rock-solid mechanical foundations. I'd also be remiss to not mention the excellent atmosphere and world building afforded by the item descriptions, monster logs, etc. RoR understands how to make a compelling mystery, and doesn't stumble over itself to provide the player with answers."
