,Recommended,248820,7773935,"Posted: 26 November, 2013",all,Azix,"I recommend this game if you are a fan of Binding of Isaac and/or you have friends that love the ""rogue-like"" idea of the gameplay. There are tons of unlockables and the game is challenging if not a bit buggy. The bugs can work for or against you, depending on how ready you are to have the same boss spawn on you infinitely...I have beat the game once and have played (and died) about 50 times or so and only have about 60% of the content unlocked. There is an abstract story line that can be paid attention to if you read the monster logs, but this isn't a game I would pick up for that reason.The classes of the game feel different enough, but there are a few that you would rather not play. This game is all about mobility and lifesteal (and all of the other buffs as well) and some of the classes are lacking in that. The first class that you get to play feels like it is the strongest so far (7 out of the 10 unlocked).This game is easily LANable for up to 4 players total. There are no public servers, you have to port forward and host yourself. I actually prefer this to the public server option as games like this are typically short-lived.PRO's:Fun, Intense, Exciting, Achieving?, Unlockables, Cheap (dollar wise)CON's:Repetitive (but, I mean...), Lack of variety/balanced classes, Bugs that make the game impossible, Difficult to set up a WAN game.82/100"
