,Recommended,248820,10119203,"Posted: 15 May, 2014",all,Welcome To The Geese Fields,"Risk of Rain is a very solid experience that doesn't hold back its punches. While the game seemed a bit harsh when I first started playing, I found that the merciless nature of the game was actually enjoyable once I got acclimated to the game. The high difficulty makes it so that any enemy encounter could be your last and whether you survive or not could come down to simply deciding to use the right ability at the right time or knowing when its time to hunker down or run for your life. Even when the game crushes you it only makes learning how to survive and making it through the game that much more rewarding. The game is also a great experience with friends, and while setting up co-op isn't the easiest thing to do in Risk of Rain, it's definitely worth the effort. The types of synergy you can pull off between characters is fantastic, as well as the variety of builds available with the many items in the game. There's always reasons to come back such as unlocking new items, hunting for artifacts, unlocking new characters, trying out every level, going for new builds, speed-running, beating the game with each character, or beating the game with friends trying out different characters. I would recommend Risk of Rain to any co-op or indie-game enthusiasts. Definitely one of my all-time favorite indie titles."
