,Recommended,248820,8217258,"Posted: 22 December, 2013",all,DJ Paradroid,"Risk of Rain just managed to squeeze in this year in my G(s)OTY2014s. Each play is a pressure-filled rogue-like romp where every second and every decision may be what finally undoes your run. As the difficulty ramps up you must decide whether to spend more time chancing the RNG to get the gear required to continue or push through until you finally reach the end. It's like Binding of Isaac if someone had a gun to your head and kept removing keyboard keys as you play.With ten classes and three difficulties it has plenty of legs and is just hard enough. You may walk away from it but you'll keep coming back if rogue-likes are your thing. It suffers slightly from Unlock Syndrome, but it's very completable.Certainly one of the best Indie titles this year. And there's been a lot of them.Too many."
