76561198075324448,Recommended,248820,13445387,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,Polar Ninja,"While the game is an incredibly enjoyable platformer/shooter roguetype, make no mistake; you will die and die again. Risk of Rain rewards players for perserverance and adaptiveness on the fly. The random enemy generation and plethora of upgrades to build a unique character each run combined with the stellar co-op multiplayer keep the game feeling fresh even after double-digit hours played. The difficulty meter that gradually raises over the course of your run is an interesting design feature, keeping you on your toes and always moving. One issue however is the sometimes monotonous way you are forced to dispatch enemies by simply kiting them. Another somewhat questionable characteristic is the balancing, or lack thereof. It is very clear that some classes are much more powerful than others.Those who can muster the will and ability to master its cruel alien terrains will find a ton of fun in this indie title. 8.0/10"
