76561198086867262,Recommended,248820,8128212,"Posted: 19 December, 2013",all,[SUPER-REDACTED],"This is a wonderful little treasure that blends relatively basic 2D platforming, rogue-like elements such as permadeath and loot collection, and a set of abilities reliant on cooldowns much like that of a moba. The combat is fluid with a wide range of abilities unique to each of the ten characters one can unlock through various means. The different passive and activatable abilities one can find within the levels are for the most part unique and offer many colorful ways of blowing your enemies to smithereens. That's another great point: the enemies. They are quite diverse with their many different abilities and ways of killing you, although some do feel like reskins at times. But the large focus on the combat deffinetly separates this game from other rogue-likes. But be warned, this game is not for the faint of heart. It can be brutally difficult, even on the easy difficulty. You must be prepared to die. A lot. All in all, this is one of my favourite games on steam and I've plugged hours of time into it. My one issue, and this is quite the glaring one, is that I have experienced severe instances of frame-rate drop, but that may be because of my computer. This game will certainly keep you busy and is a must have."
