,Recommended,248820,8731185,"Posted: 16 January, 2014",all,Ghostbear,"This game is really enjoyable. Its hard and unforgiving to begin with but once you git gud it really opens up. The different character types play  very different and you'll soon find one that you prefer. Enemies constantly spawn until you find the ""teleporter"" which spawns  the boss of that level and after 90 seconds of activating enemies will stop spawning. You must find the teleporter asap before you get overwhelmed, or you can try to farm the normal enemies for as long as possible to get money to buy items that are scattered through out the level. The challenge in the game is trying to balance this act of spawning the boss and improving your character through new  items. The game has a timer running alongside all this, that the longer the game goes on the higher the difficulty goes. So your constantly trying to juggle improving your character while fighting enemies before they become too hard. Its more enjoyable than that sounds as nearly all the items in the game stack with themselves and each other. Its not rare to have over 40 different buffs, most of which do passive things like chance on hit fire a rocket, quicker movement speed, jump jets. These things all stack so their effects get continually better. Really fun game for what you pay."
