,Recommended,248820,7795472,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,premeditated,"Risk of Rain is a pretty interesting little game, it has its bugs and issues here and there but let's be honest after the BF4 silencer, muting the whole server bug, what game doesn't these days. Let's talk about the issue at hand, Risk of Rain; there's a lot of different ways to tackle this monstrosity of a planet.The longer you take the harder the game gets and it takes this part very seriously, if you doddle or farm items for too long it can make things extremely difficult. Time equating to difficulty sure can make things interesting, as a farmer at heart it can sure make it hard to want to actually move on and continue through the stages but things can escalate extremely quickly. Items are similar to Binding of Isaac in how they unlock by completing certain feats/achievements. They also act similarly in function in that you can acquire one active use item and a number of(more than you can believe) passive stat and effect items.The game features several characters(10) to adventure through this wasteland with. You start with the commando which allows you to get quite a lot done for a base character almost to a point where sometimes I think it is better than a good few of the characters which is a bit of a con for me. The rest of the roster unlocks just like the items do, finding certain things in the world or unlocking specific achievements. The pool feels varied and interesting and if you enjoy the gameplay you will probably find yourself wanting to play the others through the game to unlock more items and any characters you need.The art style, music, and sound effects all feel very good to me but they fit my tastes and may not appeal as much to someone else. The game is primarily a singleplayer game but it also features up to 4 player local and online co-op which I have found to be a great time, the only real issue with the online is that you might have to do some network work to be able to host(open ports mainly, or turn off firewall).PROS:Flavour(art direction, music, sounds, etc.) is top notch in my opinion.Great replayability (At 20+ hours myself with about 64.5% game completion).Exciting number filled combat(Can turn off the numbers/combat text ingame if that isn't your thing).4 player co-op is great fun and classes function together in interesting ways.Has gamepad support.CONS:Port forwarding required to host.A tad buggy at times, weird issues and strict&limited graphic options.Can finish a playthrough in about 25 minutes on the easiest setting, if you don't count many many playthroughs to a game's total playtime, Risk of Rain is not for you.Some characters feel too weak or too strong.Keyboard controls can make it into Carpal Tunnel Simulator 2013 after too long of a sitting.All in all I would give Risk of Rain an 8.5/10, a quality game for $10, would like to see it get a few updates but I'm not positive on what the developer plans on doing at this point."
