76561198044024393,Recommended,248820,21820620,"Posted: 13 March, 2016",all,❃ #DatFishOffishial_,"Risk of Rain is genuinely one of my favourite games on Steam. Through the suprising lack of rain there is an masterfully crafted rouge-like that doesn't shy away from mutilating your very soul on multiple occasions. It's frustrating as hell but in genius way, every death making you want to do it all again and prove the mocking death message wrong. There is no sort of proper story like some other rouge-likes, but it doesn't need one when you are gunning the heck down avian bird thingys with the much needed help of an electric ukelele - the story is that you're a rather small pixelated guy person, just go shoot some things without worrying about why you are doing it. As mentioned before this game is frustrating, which goes hand in hand with it's pretty steep learning curve, but every death along this curve seems constructive towards you as a player. Every time a robot guy smacks you in the face you still feel a peculiar sense of accomplishment, and every time you unlock a new character you may even find yourself shedding a tear  - which is something most games can't say they do. If you just want to play the video game equivalent of frolicking in a field then this game might not be for you, but if you are one of the two people in the world looking for a frustrating way to pass the time on a rainy day (hue hue) then maybe consider giving Risk of Rain a go. You never know, you might even enjoy yourself."
