,Recommended,248820,23945221,"Posted: 29 June, 2016",all,spaceslug,"This game is hard.Unforgivingly hard.This game will punish you for breathing.In Risk of Rain, Difficulty affects not just the enemies HP, but also affects their damage dealt, the starting cash, starting health, it even affects the number Bosses that may spawn during a wave.On Drizzle difficulty, the difficulty rises one level per every 9 or so minutes. On Rainstorm, it's around 4 minutes. I don't even want to think about what may be in store on Monsoon difficulty(Difficulty rises every 3 minutes, Blighted enemies might spawn,you start with 15 gold, and the Teleporter takes 120 seconds to spawn, compared to Rainstorm and Drizzles's 90 seconds).  Progress isn't saved on Drizzle, so think of it as more of a training difficulty.Artifacts can either be a blessing or a curse, allowing you to only spawn one type of enemy per map(Kin, which is on the Dried Lake Map), to only spawning Elite class monsters(Honor, which is on the Desolate Forest Map). Ultimately, it's up to you to go for the artifacts or not, they're entirely optional and unnecessary to actually beating the game. Unless you're a Completionist. In that case, go for it. Have fun with the Map Variants.Each character has their own special usages, from the beginning class Commando, who implements his gun to move quickly and shoot just as fast, to the defense-focused Enforcer, who uses his Shield to withstand powerful attacks and can shoot faster with the Shield up with his Shotgun and Concussion Grenade.Items are vital to your survival, as you can carry any amount of items, excluding Use-Items. The Items in Risk of Rain are as numerous as they are diverse, from the simple Crowbar, which allows you to deal 50% more damage to enemies above 80% HP, to the Infusion, which gives you +1 max HP for every kill you get.In my honest opinion, this game is fantastic. I love it, it's addictive and I can't get enough of it. But be warned. It's not easy. Providence will never be your friend. To anybody who has this game or is buying/considering buying it: Kudos to you.Everybody else can suck a lemon."
