,Recommended,248820,8069963,"Posted: 16 December, 2013",all,Rush,"Risk of Rain is a 2d action platformer and has some resemblence to binding of isaac item wise. Where all the levels are the same everytime you play but the items are random. What seperates risk of rain to other 2d action platformers and makes it unique is the difficulty scale. How it works is there is no easy, medium or hard it is based on time at the start the game will start of easy but once you play more it will get difficult. This is a really great feature which stops people going back to easy levels to get more gold. There are many challenges to complete to unlock new characters with there own special features which makes each of the characters unique to play as and make you have to change you game style to suit the character your playing which adds a lot of fun to the game. What I think this game wants you to do is not just rush to complete it but see how long you surive and how much money you get at the end. I would diffently recommend this to play price is a bit steep for a game like this at £6.99 but I can look pass it due to the play back value which wants me to beat my last highscore. I rate this 7/10 would recommend if you want to try something new."
