76561198030123832,Recommended,248820,15841030,"Posted: 15 May, 2015",all,bloodmancer,"Risk of Rain is a passable addition to what I like to think of as the 'randomized indie' pantheon of games, joining titles like Binding of Isaac, Dungeons of Dredmor and Cave Story (the latter of which RoR totally feels like, down to the eerie music and exotic weaponry). The player progresses through a series of semi-randomly generated maps, mowing down all enemies in their path until they reach the titutar spaceship and escape the hazardous planet they have literally been dropped on.Pros: Each playable character feels unique, which can be a tall order in games like this. The Bandit and Commando are similar, but one has AoE and the other has knockback; HAND-E and the Merc are similar, but one has evasion and the other has healing (and nothing is really like Acrid or CHEF at all). The in-game monsters are adorable and intimidating all in one., supplemented by a gloriously presented bestiary and item log. The items combo spectacularly and there is a real sense of satisfaction as you learn the various combos and modes that the game allows you to overlay onto your experience. Games can last as long or be as short as you like. CO-OP MODE. WITH CONTROLLERS. THAT ISN'T FINICKY TO SET UP.Cons: After a few games, replaying the first levels are like pulling teeth, and it is totally possible to reach what I like to think of as the Point of Owning: for Drizzle difficulty, it's a row of items; for Rainstorm, it's two, and for Monsoon it's three rows. Once you've reached that point, the game becomes a little more trivial for the experienced platformer. The game is not even remotely balanced around Artifact of Glass or drones, even if both are insanely entertaining. Drones are also the usual culprit for screen tearing or lag, which this game has a ton of once you get a heap of items (the last possible time you'd want to lag after all that investment). The Steam achievements are very buggy and pointblank refuse to update; nor are they very reflective of the actual achievements the game offers.I give this game a 8/10 for solo controller play. If you have somebody to play with who's close to you in skill level, I'd bump that up to a 9. Simply fun."
