76561197974965249,Recommended,248820,8118776,"Posted: 19 December, 2013",all,Annihilism,"If you like roguelike action platformers than this is the game for you!You start out as a commando on an alien planet where your ship has crashed. You are the sole survivor and your goal is to defeat the final boss. The game features stages in which you have to progress to meet the final boss. You look for a teleporter in each stage and defeat the boss that spawns from it, while you are doing this multiple mobs spawn untill the timer runs out from the portal. When all the minions and the boss are dead you can go on to the next stage and fight more spawning enemies and a boss. There is a catch to all this however, the longer you take to complete a level the harder it gets. You can choose for either finding every last item in the level and try to become as powerfull as possible or to rush everything and hope you can keep up with the difficulty. If you die however you need to start from scratch.During the time you take to complete a level you earn lots of credits which you can spend on loot shrines, chests or gambling machines. Some levels also have loot spawners on which you can spend health (which can be really dangerous if you are squishy). In these loot containers you will find many great items like rocket launchers, bazookas, extra health etc. which all work passively. You can also find use items that have a very powerfull ability with a cooldown.I really like this game, the replay value is incredible and as you progress through stages and playthroughs you unluck more and more items and characters. My latest unlock was the sniper which is a very tough but fun class to play. I can definitely reccomend this game to anyone who likes roguelike platformers. This game is also very nice to play with a gamepad that has a decent D-Pad (like one of the many SNES like controller on ebay).The game can be extremely difficult (though there are some classes wich are really easy to play like the huntress) but very rewarding and does not get boring even after finishing it. It really feels like an old school 8-bit platformer.I wrote this review about a year ago and still play the game to this day. No matter how often I play it, each playthrough feels unique because of the items you find and that is really strong point of this game.Definitely one of the beste roguelike games I have ever played!"
