,Recommended,248820,23812304,"Posted: 25 June, 2016",all,Jim Halpert,"I purchased this fine piece of work and was very satisfied. It offers a wide variety of characters all with unique ablities and play styles. Although it take many hours of grinding and learning the game to unlock these characters, it was very worth it. Risk of Rain is a Rogue RPG meaning that once you die you start all over. This makes prgressing to the next level very intense knowing that your next move may kill you and make you loose all progress. The game gives gold for killing enemies found on this very strange planet. This gold can be used to open chests found in game. Inside these chests you'll find a massive variety of items which will buff your character for the duration of the world. This gives the player the chance to get a massive amount of items at once if many chests are opened allowing your character to become a monster killing machine. Although the game can be beat in maybe 40 minutes it will take lots of practice to master the skills of your character and make it to this point. at the end of every level there is a massive boss for you to take on which offers some crazy gameplay, because while the bossfight is going on there are still tons of enemies trying to kick your butt. My only complaint is that the co-op is very hard to set up and i have yet to have a chance to play this with my friends. I wish they would add easy to join co-op but besides that this game is a great pick up."
