,Recommended,248820,7662036,"Posted: 15 November, 2013",all,ESD,"First off, this is not a roguelike, nor can it be said to have ""roguelike elements"" either. So stop calling it one.It is a pure action game with randomly distributed items and premade levels that have semi-randomized structures. It is close to arcade design philosophy, but not quite. Luck plays too much of a factor in item generation, which can and will make or break runs (unless you play Huntress, because, regardless of what anyone may think or say on the matter, the ability to move while attacking puts her above everyone else in the cast) Yes, it is very possible to extend past the upper limit of the difficulty timer and become an absurd missile-spewing, marathon-running, never-dying asshat. But at that point you're more or less ruining whatever is left of the experience for yourself.What puts me off most of all is the idea of unlockables, or first and foremost, the idea that you cannot experience the game at its best until you fulfill all sorts of weird ""achievements"". It puts me off partly because I know some of you are going to BAWW at me for downloading a complete save, when the fact is I just cannot be bothered to deal with this♥♥♥♥♥♥ It's a lame excuse to wring more playtime out of the player, and the less we see of it the better. I'd rather everything be unlocked from the start and the upper difficulty limit to mean certain death, even for stupidly powerful characters, but what can I do? People are just too satisfied.I only grudgingly recommend. Play it with others."
