,Recommended,248820,27654742,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,ReverendRyu,"Not a game for the slow of thumb, Risk of Rain is a real treat when played with friends. As a small, almost tiny cluster of humanoid pixels, you must run and gun your way to the teleporter as quickly as you can, grabbing powerups as you go; and then defend the teleporter from enemy attack until you can leave. Sounds simple, no?Love it for its soundtrack, its gorgeous pixel art, its instant replayability thanks to PLD, for its creativity and zest. Hate it for the sheer controller-bending frustration you will feel just clearing the first level. Love a good platformer? Like a great schmup? Love generally amazing things? Breathe Oxygen? This game is for you."
,Recommended,248820,17806078,"Posted: 30 August, 2015",all,Howl J. Pendragon,"One problem I've had with many roguelites would be the combat. Sometimes they didn't offer the weight and impact that make attacking and killing things feel good.Risk of Rainis one roguelite that gets that right. Attacks and explosions come with appropriate recoil and visceral feedback. The game gets this and many other things right.Each character has four abilities, giving unique flavor and utility to their gameplay. The character diversity gives great incentive for replayability since it'll be necessary to unlock everything. Furthermore, there are TONS of items that all bring creative, diverse effects to your attacks. Some items just buff your stats, but others have more interesting effects such as turning the enemies you kill into temporary ghost allies.The flow of the game works well, too. You need to kill enemies, get money, power up, and find the exit as soon as possible. The longer you take, the higher the difficulty goes. You'll die a lot, but it's part of the fun and you'll be eager to return.If there's one complaint I have with the game, it would be the ambiguity with some of the item descriptions. While you can view more detailed effects through the main menu, some of the flavor text can make understanding your items more difficult than it needs to be.Interesting items, beefy combat effects, and clear risk come together for a great experience. It's definitely one of the best roguelites around."
