76561198076514263,Recommended,248820,12029820,"Posted: 8 September, 2014",all,thewebb414,"Risk of Rain simply put is a rougelike game that is fun to play over and over again.The game uses simple controls to put you in the shoes of one of 10 classes (all but 1 must be unlocked through gameplay) that have found themselves stranded on a strange planet full of creatures bent on killing them. Your goal is to find a teleporter hidden somewhere that will allow you to progress further and find your crashed ship and leave the planet.The game is rougelike so Perma-death is a MAJOR feature. every time you die you lose all progress from that playthrough (bar certain things unlocked from achievments) and have to start again the next go around. This doesn't turn out to be a big deal though as every time you load the game the stages and their layouts will have changed.Every Class in the game has there own unique style of combat from meele to ranged to hybrids of the two allowing for varying styles of gameplay and many ways to fight the same enemies in a new and challenging way, and the dozens of enemy types will make each stage a diffrent experience from the last.The best part of this game though in my opinion is the multiplayer. The ability to play online or localy with up to 4 players makes the game even more interesting to beat because of the added ability to combo the diffrent classes together and finding things you wouldn't have alone.Overall if you enjoy games with LOTS of replayablity and LOTS of random challenges this is a must grab that will have you playing for hours on end."
