,Recommended,248820,23988943,"Posted: 1 July, 2016",all,iSpook,"Let me start this review by saying I love this game. But it isn't without its faults either.Since I'm not good at writing reviews I'll go with the classic ""pros/cons"" format and follow it up with suggestions how to improve on negative points. Also there are some points which can be considered pros and cons at the same time, depending on how you play games.Pros:-Price (even at 10 bucks its worth it, at a sale even more so)-Replayability (potentially infinite levels to go through)-Challenging, the intensity slowly ramps up and you gives you just enough time to gather enough power ups-Beautiful-Almost no power up feels useless and they're all useful in their own regards-Character diversity-End Boss battle is actually pretty hard if you do it before getting too powerful-Unlocking stuff can be hard to achieve but is very rewarding although some secrets like the Miner can be hard to find-Rounds can go on for as long as you likeCons:-I guess it's hard to play multiplayer since you need something like Hamachi for it and it can be a pain for some people to set that up-You can actually become too powerful. If you play long enough you can't be killed at a certain point anymore because of the lifesteal/hp/armor power up and the fact that they stack.-Some characters feel useless and by that I mean you find yourself thinking:""Why would I play this one when I can play the Archer""-If your friend dies in co-op the xp and item loss is ridiculous for them to the point where they might as well leave the game (then again, if you die once playing solo the game is over too)-Rounds can be longConclusion:I fell in love with this game the first time I played it and every friend I recommended it to liked it aswell. Seeing it on the sale moved me to write a review and made me wish they made some DLC. I might have forgotten some points since I haven't played it for some time but I have only good memories of it. Get it (if the genre speaks to you) and you will not be disappointed."
