,Recommended,248820,7809750,"Posted: 28 November, 2013",all,Mellow Bordello,"Risk of rain is a fantastic Rougelike. It features randomized level (To some extend) which greatly extends gameplay. The progrssion in the game is very slow, so expect to spend countless hours in the risk of rain to unlock all the characters. This keeps the game from becoming dull when shooting becomes too much. This is also a fantastic addition to the games multiplayer component, which is a 2-4 player co-op mode. In this mode the players cooperates with up to 3 friends to complete the games levels. The players share both XP and money.The game has a fantastic loot system, that adds both random effects and buffs to your character. These upgrades keeps the game fresh and fast paced, since every game is different. No other games seems to do exactly what this game does, and if they do, they are probably not as good.The other interesting component to the game is the timer. The game features a leveling system wich power you up as you play through and kill monsters. This backside of this leveling is the timer, which keep you moving. As time goes on, the game becomes significantly harder if you stay in a place and farm money, XP and drops. This tactic is therefore ill advised."
