,Recommended,248820,11649141,"Posted: 11 August, 2014",all,GunterGunts,"This is honestly worth the simple 10 bucks. Plenty of classes, items, areas, enemies and bosses, and random spawns. Most of all, plenty of challenge. For me, its style and execution worked surprisingly well together, sprite-art [best art :3] with random spawned everything on a difficulty that increased every 5 minutes? It works extremely well. On the difficulty, it stops at nice little level labled ""HAHAHAHA"", but the difficulty doesn't there. Even after filling the bar, the clock is still agaisnt you. As for the enemies, each one is diverse and usually match the area. From Bighorn Bison charging short distances to deal massive damage, to a giant frackin turtle that shoots artillary in a volcano. Each class requires a different style, and none of them come close another. You have ranged classes and melee classes, each with different base stats and scaling, excluding items. The items...well...are a whole different review. Seriously. Just...look at the screenshot to see how many there are. Then each one is different. The runes may be taken as cheats....but you work for them. You work really...really....REALLY hard for them, and they are well earned bonuses. Either adding extra challenge or extra control of what you get. All and all, great game for those who appreciate sprite-art and getting fairly angry at a small window that repeatedly kills you, and then tells you what you do after death or that it's your fault. Get. The. Game. 10 bucks, come on. Just. Do it."
