,Recommended,248820,12881366,"Posted: 10 November, 2014",all,Wefflez,"Best purchase on steam without a doubt. An intensely immersive game that I could not stop playing. It started out as just another rogue-like game with a little twist made by a couple of guys who just wanted to make a game. It turned into a game that drives in not only intense difficult gameplay, but fast paced decision making and a strangely immersive plot. The gameplay, made by people who have obviously played or at least heard of Dota 2 and LoL, is like combining a sidescrolling platformer with a moba and a rogue-like. The game stays completely unique with a vast number of items, enemies, and characters. The longer you play the game, the harder it gets.....literally.....the difficulty increases the longer the run. The game feels to work like a rogue-like where the enemies are super overpowered after the first level, but the items you get are even more overpowered. It's like fighting over power on a much larger scale than I have ever seen before in a rogue-like game. The makers of this game put so much time into it that I feel like I'm still not doing the game justice by completing 89% of it. I can't stress how much this game can play with you emotionally (the music writer is a goddamn genius on the last stage). I'm stopping this review here because there is too much to say and I have already said enough, but I highly recommend purchasing this game. It is, and will remain, in my top games list. I am never changing my magma worm background, no matter how poorly the JPG is compressed and scaled ;D."
