,Recommended,248820,7860385,"Posted: 1 December, 2013",all,Ultric,"Let me just start with this: Get this game.Risk of Rain is a roguelike, which I've basically learned to mean a game where you have one life and it plays differently every time. This crazy awesome little game has a fantastic mix of powerups, ranging from Barbed Wire which does a little bit of damage to people around you to the Ceremonial Dagger which rewards each kill with several ridiculously powerful bolts that will more than likely kill something else on the map, close or far. Or maybe you'd be more interested being able to trail fire everywhere you walk. Heck, do all three!The game includes a bunch of bosses that require different ways of dealing with them. The Wandering Vagrant may seem easy to avoid, but wait until you've got 8 of them bearing down on you with 4 health bars each. The longer you play the game, the harder it gets. If you stick around too long in any stage, the next one may start by politely spawning about 8 bosses for you to fight even before you activate the escape timer. Seriously, 8 Magma Worms aren't easy to kill.There's a multitude of unlockable characters, each with their own unique and enjoyable playstyle. Want to skillfully one-shot bosses? Be the Sniper. Want to poison and slaughter hordes of enemies using poison that happens to boost your speed like a cheerful child being pushed in a shopping cart? Bring Acrid along. Want to be the ultimate Rock-em Sock-em Robot? HAN-D will happily beep and boop to create a soundtrack for your warpath.Want to know the best part? I've beaten the game 5 times and I'm still seeing new things for the first time that keep coming around and kicking my butt.Buy it. Play it. Love it."
