76561198015015741,Recommended,248820,20491004,"Posted: 12 January, 2016",all,evil_paris,"Despite its simple graphics, Risk of Rain is a wickedly good roguelike and you should own it.The game features an assortment of classes, which gradually unlock as you default challenges within the game.   The classes change how you interact with the levels, and provide additional replayability on top of what is already a compelling game.Basic gameplay involves simple combat, exploration, and tradeoff choices in how to spend your resources.  There are boatloads of upgrades of various rarities, many of which are stackable which can be anything from a minor boost, to a hugely impacting laser sweep or exploding enemies.There's a constant time pressure, as the random encounter difficulty scales up the longer you play.  So while you may find yourself tempted to just park and farm on a particular low level, even that will eventually become uncomfortable, and the next level will be brutal because of it.  You either rush forward, and content yourself with fewer items but a better your level : monster level ratio, or take it slow and fight better equipped against harder foes.  It is well balanced and makes for a good tradeoff.Each level type contains a distinct set of enemies, with randomized placement and individual feature tweaks.  The game has lots of challenges which unlock new dropped items, gameplay modifiers (usually tradeoffs that you can decide to play with), and classes.I admit I'm one of those people who generally feels a game is complete when I've unlocked every achievement for the game.  Risk of Rain is one of those games that even after I have long since done this, I still find myself picking it up to play randomly regardless."
