76561198124424462,Recommended,248820,8896004,"Posted: 28 January, 2014",all,Iron Booty,This game gud. Good game this is. Very much so a good game. I like game more tahn fam e. Really buy this game for so much fuin.
,Recommended,248820,8755707,"Posted: 18 January, 2014",all,ShinyHobo,Words cannot describe how much I love this game.
,Recommended,248820,8667515,"Posted: 11 January, 2014",all,Akarinata,"First of all, let me just say that I haven't writtien a review since the the required review for the Pillar of Community Steam badge. I've always planned to write more, but I wanted to make my next one way more meaningful than the first. So, here I am.  This should already say something about how great this game is.Risk of Rain is one of the best games I've ever played (And I've played on every platform, and over thousands of games). It blends co-op, roguelike elements, challenge, and good old fun in one, amazing, already low-priced package. The soundtrack is great; so much so that I was always stuck listening to it in my head, until I eventually took the files from within the game itself and copied them to my phone to listen to them when away from my pc.Whether you like playing solo or going through games with a friend, you'll find there's challenge in both, no matter the skill. The game's difficulty slowly increases with time...after the 40 minute mark, you've just about hit the highest difficulty. However, if being challenged isn't your thing, you can always just choose the 'Easy' difficulty at the character screen, and difficulty will climb slower, but you won't be able to earn achievements this way. The challenge is to get farther than you did your last attempt, and to collect as many loot items along the way, to fill your logbook, which in itself I've spent many hours just reading the hidden and not-so-hidden references in the backstory of Risk of Rain. Each item has a unique effect, and different descriptions. Some items can only be found within the game after completing certain parameters shown in the logbook. New classes can also be unlocked this way.Even if you don't like reading, and prefer just going in and shooting things, Risk of Rain will sate you. After 5 mintues into the game, you're already guarenteed to be running for your life, blasting what you can as you try and evade everything trying to kill you. Each class in the game has unique abilities, and offers different playstyles, suitable for different types of players. Personally, I like being a gunslinger, and sneaking, so naturally, I love Bandit and Commando. Commando is your basic, starting class, and is actually arguably the best class of the game, if you know how to use him to his full extent. However, that doesn't mean that your class can't be the best in your hands. Commando is only the most balanced, and a good starting point for every type of player. But as you get into the unlockable classes, you'll eventually find one that suits you, if the first few aren't your style.The art in this game was also really outstanding, and inspiring. Pixel art isn't easy to pull off well; yet Risk of Rain's dev team did an amazing job of spinning a story within the art itself. Personally, it inspired me to do more art, and more writing. I don't think the game will ever look dated...This game could easily look as something from the 90's, yet something from any future generation with its fast gameplay, and creativity. If you appreciate any kind of digital art, you'll be lost and immersed in the game's visuals itself. This may be a little unrelated, but the soundtrack just added onto the ambience so well when enjoying this game, and the art.All in all, the game is easily worth the money invested into it. Every game is different, no two playthroughs are the same, and your luck can be all good or all bad in any playthrough, but ultimately, you can control your destiny in the game with your skills. The game really reminded me of Dark Souls with the challenge it gives you, and the gameplay itself feels like a classic sidescroller, yet with more magic and originality than most. The game is easily a classic of its own, and I believe will withstand the test of time in this coming generation of games, and even afterwards."
