,Recommended,248820,9801234,"Posted: 12 April, 2014",all,Valk 93,"Let me start this off by saying that this game is amazing fun and a definite must have.Now for a real review.Risk of Rain is a mix of a platformer, a rogue-lite and action. The player is dropped off on a strange and hostile planet after a crash with their spaceship. You set out as one of 10 characters that made an emergency landing far from the ship to make your way back to that very ship. Your goal is to survive the journey there, taking you through at least 5 levels (with 10 different ones) on the way. Reaching the ship will take quick thinking, combat capabilities and guts. Without these, you will not survive.Risk of Rain plays through (mostly) randomly generated levels where death means death. No quickloading, no respawn points, nothing. You die you start over. On your way through the levels your character gains experience and money from killing enemies. Experience levels your character up and boosts it's stats (like health, damage output, HP regen etc). Money is spent on either chests for random items, vending stations to pick from 3 items, or on shrines to try your luck for an item. Items are either passive or 'use' items, and will prove valueable on your journey. Every item has it's own unique trait, and gathering as much as you can will definitly aid your survival.Every level is filled with different enemies, from rock golems to big-horners (I hate these) to robot Temple Guardians. Each with their own attacks and strategy to approach. At the end of every level a teleporter awaits, setting in motion the final stage of a level. During 90 seconds the entire place fills up with enemies as well as a boss. Once are all defeated, the player can look around some more to pick up any items they might've forgotten (or couldn't afford yet) or progress to the next level.The beauty about the game is how every playthrough is different. Every character has their own 4 unique moves and playstyle. Every enemy has their own unique attack and traits. Every boss requires a different strategy to take down. And in the end it's all about that final encounter with the very being that destroyed your ship. Will you defeat him, or fall before him?Risk of Rain is amazing and I love it. 9/10"
