,Recommended,248820,13022068,"Posted: 20 November, 2014",all,solhesten,"One of my favourite games for quite a while. I'm not even sure where to start.Its a very challenging and engaging game. You'll die again and again, and learn from it.Every playable character (about 10 of them, and will be unlocked as you progress through the game and do achievements) have 4 ""basic"" abilites, which I always kind of related to moba games, altho mostly in how the abilities are presented.The first one is a basic, low cooldown attack which you can spam.The rest of them can vary between different kinds of dashes, blinks, aoe abilities and I could keep going. The point is that every kit fits the character extremely well, and despite it might seem simple at first glance, you'll eventually have (and will) master the kit if you want to survive long enough to win the game.There is three difficulties to choose between, and when you get into the game, there is another difficulty bar - which will progressively be harder as time goes by and will eventually lead to bosses and elite creeps  spawning.This means you'll have to maximize the amount of gold you receive per level, so you can get as many items as you can on one level, while finishing the level as fast as possible so you wont waste time, and end up at a hard difficulty with few items (which are essential to survival).Speaking of items, there is a huge arsenal of different passive items, which have varying degrees of usefullness depending on what character you play as. Getting basic attack speed buffs, wont do you much good on a bolt sniper, but it might be good on others that are more dps focused. In that way, your build can vary in many ways (There are artifacts you can find, which among others, will make you able to specifically pick items, rather than getting random drops everytime - which is the norm).Other than passive items, there are also a bunch of different actives, with a world of different uses - and works a lot like of your 4 basic abilities, but with a much longer cooldown.It is very much worth mentioning it has both local and online coop available - although I havent found that to be very balanced, mostly due to its hard splitting items up, as you wont get much more gold despite being two or more people. Its still very fun however.I personally love the ""simplifed"" pixel artstyle the game has, and has a lot of charm to it.Lastly, but almost most importantly, the soundtrack by Chris Christodoulou, is insanely good. I've played for 50+ hours I think, and listened to the soundtrack outside of the game as well, and I'm still not bored of it.(Chanson d'Automne will always have a special place in my heartAlso, you can beat giant magma worms up as a guy with huge fists. So satisfying.Updated with artifacts that change the gameplay, adds even more content to the game. Possible to local/online coop as well."
