,Recommended,248820,8433064,"Posted: 30 December, 2013",all,cunt,"There are 2 sections of this game: Hard and Harder.When you first start off, you may be like ""Pshh, there is only like 5 enemies, how could this possibly be bad?"" but the moment 4 Collossi stomp on you at once and your character gets blasted upwards, do you realize how wrong you were. This game has 3 gamemodes, 12 characters (each wonderfully thought out), over 100 items, minimalistic but interesting story, and 10 artifacts to further change up the game. Needless to say, there is quite a large amount of replayability. This game also has a kind of gimmick, if you will. As time increases, so does your difficulty. This feature prevents farming as items are the most helpful thing in the game but only so many spawn on each level, forcing you to leave it sooner rather than later. You have to survive through about 4 or 5 (i forget) levels until you can go to the last one, which is your crashed ship from the opening ""cinematic"". Risk of Rain's art style is nothing to write home about, but it gets the job done and is actually kind of awesome at some points (only a very few select points.) There are also a large amount of items to be unlocked so even if you beat the game 100 times, you may not have unlocked everything, giving you bigger goals.tl;dr there is a lot of stuff to do in this game and difficulty increases as time does. Have Fun!"
