76561198043573904,Recommended,248820,7880385,"Posted: 2 December, 2013",all,"Bright ""Chimera""","I'll keep this quick, much like the game. Risk of Rain is in my opinion an amazingly fun, fast paced side scrolling, shoot 'em up, beat them down, pixel art styled game with plenty of appealing game mechanics, rogue like aspects and lore to keep you having fun for a good while /on your own/. If you can manage to get some friends to play with /without/ lag issues out the♥♥♥♥♥ you're in for the ride of your life. This game will make you laugh, it will make you cry. You'll feel accomplished at times after barely scruffing it out with a boss, and other times you'll feel like you had no chance, overwhelmed, humbled and defeated.Risk of Rain will make you cry, either out of joy or pure dismay. Each play through is livened up by the randomly generated items, and you'll find some are great on their own to rely on while others need to synergize with certain other items. Overall, it is a great game, and it has 10 characters to choose from. Each character, might I add, has completely different play styles from the others in my opinion, and I honestly can't say one is /better/ than the other.Overall, I give it 9 and a half Screes out of 10, because holy hot hell and damn this game is amazing and I love the artwork, atmosphere and do not even get me STARTED on the music soundtrack. If they touched up a few issues I have with the game (glitches, lag issues, and muliplayer achievement bugs) then it'd easily be a 10/10."
