76561198012914016,Not Recommended,248820,32950037,Posted: 28 June,all,Cpt._Baseballbat-Boy,"Of all the many, many roguelikes for sale, this one is strikingly mediocre. It commits the worst sin of all for this genre: it gets tedious fast. It may be pretty tough, but only in the sense of the enemies having way too much health for you to beat them in a satisfying fashion. The gameplay is monotonous, with every character playing the same, using your abilities in a never changing rhythm. Plus, you are forced to abuse your dodge mechanic to a silly degree. In this game, dodging is your bread, butter, knife and fork.The item pool is rather limited as well, and there are little to no synergies to find or tinker with.The maps are very large, and if you are unlucky, you will have to backtrack through them, in case you missed the teleporter by venturing in the wrong of two directions. This is not very helpful, or interesting, considering you are on a timer.All in all, there are so many more interesting, creative and fun roguelikes out there, that you should definitely not spend any amount of money on this one."
