76561197996051698,Recommended,248820,16503914,"Posted: 18 June, 2015",all,Biggus Dickus,"Risk Of Rain is without a doubt one of my favorite rogue likes. It really has the feel of an old shcool Super Nintendo or Genesis game and is brutally difficult to boot. This game will make you tear your hair out sometimes, its unforgiving and hard to be good at let alone master. Every character plays differently, very differently and its always interesting trying a new one. They all have fun skills and abilities and all of them seem viable with enough practice. When you finally get into the grove with a certain class you'll really feel like badass as you fight for minutes on end with the same 3x or 4x over leveled enemies in massive swarms. The aesthetic is really fun to watch in motion and is really quite pretty in action. Seeing your enemies keel over after being riddled with bullets and fall into a pile of bits and blood is always satsifying. Adding to that satisfaction is the sound of the weapons, explosions and monsters in this game, great sound design.When I bought Risk of Rain I kind of expected a game more in line with mobile games and cheap games that you might put a few hours in once in a while. It took those expectations and ripped them a new ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥, just like the game did to me on my first playthrough. The combat is so engaging, and the rogue-like elements are so solid in this game that I personally have almost no complaints in regards to gameplay or visuals. And again, the sound in this game, the music is fantastic and if you're the kind of person who likes video game soundtracks then you'll probably like it too. Every track is a winner and pairs so well with the environment its being played on. The visual style, levels and back drops in this game blend so well with the music and with engaging combat it can be mesmerizing. Everything adds to the other worldly feel of this game and that feeling of imminent death. Something about this game, inspite of its difficulty, keeps me coming back for more time and time again like a masochist. For a little game that costs $10 its worth every penny and I hope these devs go on to more projects. This is one of the best rogue-likes out there for my money and I keeping coming back for long sessions over and over.If you like challenging games and if you like rogue-likes then take a risk and grab this game.Risk of Rain is everything that reminds me why video games are just awesome sometimes, with or without state of the art graphics and effects.9/10"
