,Recommended,248820,7914664,"Posted: 4 December, 2013",all,みoƦƦoƦ ₣o父,"Hey everyone and welcome to my review about this game!This is a Rogue-like side-scrolling Action game.Inferface/Settings/Menu.There is Local Co-op and online Co-op. (However i am not sure if the online function still works).Online Co-op Does require IP and Port forwarding.There is an Item/Monster log. (Just a reminder what each item does and monster information).You can play this game with a xbox controller.You can change controls on the keyboard and Controller.You can change the resolution Size.You can play this fullscreen or Window mode.You can change the Volume to sound and Music. It goes as in %, So 10%, 20% 30%There is a Score and Unlockables Menu. There are also Challenges at the Unlockables Tab.About the game.This is a rogue-like game and each run will be different everytime you will be playing. There is a variety in characters and some characters can be unlocked by fulfilling the requirements. Each character has their own playstyle and equipment. Own Advantage and disadvantage, Own stats and Combo's. You will notice their is a time limit on the right side. This is the ""Difficulty meter"" and as the name says it. The difficulty will be increased and the game will be harder the longer you are in a run.There is no storyline.The Graphics are okay.The Music is decent and changes per level.Has Many unlockable Characters.Each character plays differently.There is an ingame time difficulty, Level Difficulty and artifact Difficulty.There is a level up system and (Monster) item drops available.Has Some Collectables.Experience and gold will automatically be collected, no need to gather them.There are chests/crates/shops and statues available.Falling off the world will teleport you back up and you will take some damage. (Enemies dies)There is Fall Damage.There are some Hidden/Secrets in the game.You will have to start at the beginning if you are going to leave a run.Other things.It's not always good to stay too long on one level. The game difficulty becomes higher and higher the longer your run. However Farming isn't always a bad thing.With Commando: If you think you are going to take Fall damage, Try to use the Roll Ability on time to avoid taking the Fall damage. (You can't take damage if you are Rolling. From no source).Also GET THE DYNAMITE ACTIVE ON THIS DUDE. IT'S SOO POWERFUL. You kill bosses in no-time.  A well-timed Roll from the commando is able to dodge the damage from falling off the world.Do not underestimate the drones that you might find. They do some serious damage. Especially when stacked up. (especially against bosses when you are more active with running the doing damage). You won't lose the drones if you have completed a level, just do be careful that you need to repair them with cash if they are destroyed.Enemies will not spawn in ""hidden/secret/fake"" walls.Holding the Space bar button on ""elevator jumps"" will let you fly higher.Magma Worm boss never seem to hurt the player if it is climbing on a rope or a Ladder.Let's try Video:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gCjPi3i21N4I will give this game a 7/10"
,Recommended,248820,7787652,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,Frightening Forik,"I was waiting for Starbound, the other day, when on the Chucklefish website this game was announced. Thinking it was some sort of weatherman simulator, I instantly purchased it, and have not regretted a penny spent on it since. I'll get the negative out of the way first, the game has no trains, and it is no weatherman simulator. I was also very disappointed to see that there was no actual rain despite the fact that the game's name indicates there being some possibility of it. However, on to the positive. I irked several of my friends to get this game and play it with me, but the select few that didn't remove me off their friend's list for telling them to buy this game every ten minutes were thoroughly pleased with it. And we had thirty-something hours of fun the first day the game was out. The game is very reminiscent of The Binding of Isaac, but of course, it's an action platformer shooty game instead of a top-down shoot 'em up styled game. That's not to say that there's no shoot 'em up elements in Risk of Rain. Whenever you're not shooting things, you're avoiding them. The game is tons of fun with friends, and I would definitely recommend it to anybody who likes a good and light experience where you shoot stuff and get items to shoot more stuff with."
