76561198046857476,Recommended,248820,16616001,"Posted: 22 June, 2015",all,Alex,"Risk of Rain is one of the perfect games to play when you have a good hour or so to breeze through. It is a roguelike where the longer you are alive the harder the game becomes. Each stage has chests and a portal to the next stage. You earn money by killing things and when you are done with a stage you have to survive for 90 seconds as an increased number of enemies spawn. Once you've killed everything in the level you progress to the next stage and do it all over again until the fourth stage, at which point you have the choice to go back through the stages to gain more items or to progress to the final stage. The game has a number of varied characters, my personal favorite being the huntress, that you unlock by fighting specific bosses or doing challenges. The items you pick up throughout the game come in a number of varieties, white, green, yellow, red, orange, and purple. White, green, and red are normal items going up in rarity that can be bought or found in chests, yellow items are boss items that you have a chance of getting from bosses bestowing a power that the boss used, orange are usable items that can be found similarly to regular items, and purple items are hidden relics that change the base stats of the player and monsters around them as well as other effects that can make the game harder or easier. Each stage is varied and have unique designs that are beautiful to look at while not being distracting from the action. The final stage has many different side paths to take that can unlock different items and some machines that can be used against the final boss to make it an easier battle. The final boss goes through many different stages and it is a steady challenge, especially towards the 50 minute mark. The only real negatives I can think of from the game is that the multiplayer never really worked well for me and despite having gotten all the achievements in the game some of them did not unlock on my steam profile.TL;DR Excellent Roguelike with a lot of different characters, enemies, and items."
