,Recommended,248820,9663973,"Posted: 29 March, 2014",all,VisibleDucts,"Beautiuful 2D 'platformer' graphics (sidescroller?), fun action shooter with skills to add strategy making it more than running and gunning. Skills you need to have any chance of staying alive. For longer than you would without them. But you will die. It's a brutal game with permadeath, the roguelike aspect of the game. Normally, I might say this is a roguelike-like (rogue-lite, as the kids say I think. A game that isn't a roguelike but is influenced by them and uses roguelike mechanics in a unique way but isn't really a roguelike in the ""pure"" sense), however, in various ways it meets what I consider the core criteria of the roguelike genre. It's not turn based, but I think that's a standard roguelike feature, not a core one. It has a high difficulty level, classes with differnet skills, various items you find throughout the stages, and although there are no potions or items that are ""cursed"" (so far, in my playthroughs) - those things in roguelikes can be abstracted to the role they play: random danger from items that could be beneficial but you don't know until you use them. Risk of Rain has ""shrines"" that you pay to use, the shrines increase in cost with each use and you are not guarenteed anything - it's random and they could be really beneficial, and then sometimes it's just a waste of gold, and other times they can hurt you. They fulfill the role, to an extent, that unidentified items in more 'standard' roguelikes fulfill. Oh, and of course permadeath. Risk of Rain also starts off difficult (although after you play for awhile, the start of a game becomes a lot easier), however, it uses a timer feature that increases the diffculty the longer you're alive/in a stage (I can't honestly confirm if it resets when you activate the teleporter and go to the next stage since I've died at the last few seconds of the countdown when the teleporter is activating on the first level....) - when you start it tells you by the timer that it's ""very easy"", which in comparison to later difficulty ramps, is true. Very easy compared to what I think when I hear the term ""very easy"" though? Not so much...Anyway, it's a great game, well worth it if you like challenging, pretty, roguelikes with a twist. Oh, and playing with a gamepad is so much better than using a keyboard, in my experience..."
