,Recommended,248820,12852107,"Posted: 8 November, 2014",all,ScorpioTheConqueror,"Short Answer: Great game but not for people who aren't very good at video games or just don't like Rogue-Lite's that are incredibly hard.Long Answer:I love this game, I may only have 13.3 hours on record but I know enough about the game to review it.Risk of Rain is a VERY VERY VERY VERY VERY hard rogue-lite that will take you a long time to beat, there are many items and classes to unlock which just adds to the sheer awesomeness of the game.Does this game have a story? Well, yes. But in no way is it story driven. You're on a spaceship and some bloody ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ called Providence comes and blows it up, you're the only survivor and you land on a planet. Please tell me if I'm missing something.Does this game have a combat system? HELL. TO. THE. YES. This games combat system is so great and engaging, each class has four abilities. One is just the primary attack and the other three are the special attacks (Fun fact: You'll be disappointed when you unlock the Engineer) which are usually awesome.Every class is different, from a arrow-launching Huntress to a thick armoured Enforcer they're all very unique.There are also game changing artifacts you can find and once you find them you can activate them when you begin the game like a glass cannon one which I won't spoil the effect of.This game is great but does it have flaws? Yes. It's too hard. I know you'll get used to it, but it's so intense and hard that it keeps me from playing, I have to play in small short doses. (Usually 20-60 mins per session) Also, the controls are kinda wirey but they can be rebinded.Also the music is AMAZING!!! It's just so good... You'll have to see for yourselves.The graphics are meh, they're okay.The final verdict for Risk of Rain is... 8.5/10. The hardness really takes away some of the game for me but it's still amazing and very recommended!Until the next review :)"
