,Recommended,248820,7695242,"Posted: 19 November, 2013",all,BrightOrangePants,"A delightful roguelike experience.  This lovely little platformer nails the ""easy to learn, hard to master"" gameplay and doesn't let up on the difficulty.  You play as one of ten classes each with four abilities/attacks, and simply try to survive as long as possible.You scour each level in search of a teleporter to the next, leveling up along the way.  You must hurry, because the difficulty is tied to how long you are taking, with it ramping up in five-minute increments.  Its item system borrows heavily from The Binding of Isaac, there's no stat building, just strap items on as you go.  The music is also nice.  This is absolutely worth your time if you like the roguelike genre.  Or even if you dont!  It's a nice lightweight timewaster or a keyboard-smashingly difficult experience, depending on the difficulty you choose."
