76561198100173444,Recommended,248820,7955357,"Posted: 7 December, 2013",all,Vanadate,"Risk of Rain is well worth the purchase. It's brutal in the absolute best possible way, it doesn't cut you any slack but never feels unfair or cheap. When you die (which you will) it always feels like its your fault and there's something you could have done better to survive that little bit longer. Its immensely re-playable due to the random nature of the levels, although this is mostly through item type and placement rather than the actual layout itself. The pacing of the game is excellent, the early stages build up your confidence as you cut down the occasional enemy but as time goes on your plight becomes more and more desperate, until you're engaged in a frantic dash for survival during the boss fights.Rounds are between 20-30 minutes in length, which makes it perfect for dipping into when you don't feel like sinking your teeth into something heavier. Adjusting the difficultly actually changes the whole feel of the game, going easier results in a very satisfying ""god mode"" with a huge array of items turning you into a powerhouse, whilst going harder is a constant adrenalin rush. I confess I'm not actully good enough to make any real progess on the hardest difficulty but its fun in a mascohistic way regardless. Credit must also go to the soundtrack, which is phenomenal and deeply atmospheric. The pixel art style is different and certainly striking, though might not be to everyone's taste but doesn't diminish the game at all.My only minor compliant is that the ballance in the items can seem a bit off. Some are incredibly situational, bordering on useless whilst others are fantasic and near certain choices. Although the random nature of the game can result in you getting screwed over from time to time, it doesn't happen very often.In short, a fantastic game which I'll probably still play years down the line, highly recommended."
