,Recommended,248820,20654545,"Posted: 20 January, 2016",all,Blight,"Bought Risk of Rain when it was on sale... One of the best decisions i've ever made. If you're like me and like a challenging game that kind of tilts the tables of progress and difficulty, then this might just be the game for you. I never really got into platformers, always felt they were a bit too slow for me on gameplay but this game brings a fresh new look on platformers. First off, choose your survivor with unique abilities. Load one of the first maps which are random, find items, level up, and make sure to find the teleporter. Activate the teleporter and be ready for a HEAVY enemy wave filled with loads of mininons and as well a massive boss. Once clearing out all enemies, escape through the portal. Now, I know that sounds a bit linear but, what this game has going for it is that the longer you look around looting for items, the harder the game gets. It's up to you to figure out how will you be managing your time. Loot too long, enemies become ever more O.P., rush through the level and be ready to be unprepared for what the game will throw your way next. Did I mention that it's 4-player co-op? Online and local 4 player co-op are what makes this game really shine. Grab some mates, suit up as different characters, get out of the escape pod and take your first steps on this alien planet, gather items, and prepare yourselves to fight back to back against the unforgiving hordes of aliens that want nothing more to see you fall. Oh almost forgot, once you die, it's GAME OVER... G.L."
