,Recommended,248820,32485986,Posted: 16 June,all,malaisling,"A fantastic and simply designed rogue-like in which players fight their way through hordes of enemies, gathering statistic and effect influencing items while advancing to new locations in an attempt to escape the planet.The game includes a variety of characters to play from, who each have a completely unique array of abilities used to fight which each focus around a relatively unique style of combat from the other characters. While the pool of acquirable items is rather small compared to other rogue-likes, unlike other rogue-likes nearly every item is useful in some way. And, you can acquire multiple of the same item in order to stack its effect to become even more powerful. The potential builds created from stacking the same item repeatedly well making up for the lack of item diversity in terms of interesting possibilities.While the map randomization, map types, bosses and enemies are all rather limited, once again compared to other rogue-likes, it does not damage the replayability to any significant degree.And while there are some inconveniences in the map design and platforming, but it is not very severe and the game plays quite well.The primary issue the game has that is mentionable is the lack of a significant post game. The final boss, is the final boss, and after the player defeats him the sense of purpose in replaying the game does start to feel lost. Even with new characters and items to unlock, after the initial victory the game does not feel nearly as replayable as other more popular rogue-likes out there as the structure of the game progression and randomization itself is not as comparable. And although the game does feature online co-op, it requires a quite tedious and technical setup in order to orchestrate it and so it is not very dependable in terms of accessibility.But in all, well worth the cost for the amount of strong and well designed gameplay the player will get out of it."
