76561198039683273,Not Recommended,248820,9973531,"Posted: 29 April, 2014",all,Winter Road,"More tedious than fun. I enjoy playing skill based perma-death games similar to this, but many aspects of this game feel quite un-fun. The variation among enemies is scarce, and most monsters just try to run into you en-mass. Like FTL, this game requires a good bit of luck finding the right upgrades for your particular character early enough to make full use of them. Unlike FTL, each class only has a limited field strategy. A given class will have four skills and even though simpler games, like Binding of Isaac, offer less options, the supplementary power-ups leave you wanting more. The monsters in general seem to have too much health, and can be quite tedious to kill at mid to higher levels unless all the appropriate power-ups are gained. In addition, some power-ups seems strictly better than others, regardless of class; which I feel is poor design. The size of the characters and monsters seems unnecessarily small, and becomes bothersome at times. The size of the sprites creates of lack of character when compared to games like Rogue Legacy and Binding of Isaac. Overall its just not as charming or addictive as the game seems to think it is."
76561198065827209,Not Recommended,248820,12653732,"Posted: 27 October, 2014",all,CGG Zayik,"Risk of Rain is a retro style game that suits well to those who just want to mindlessly destroy things. It has a variety of unlockable character (which is rare in most games, be it big or small). The gameplay is fun, and it's definitely a fun game to play with a buddy . . . that is if you are lucky to not encounter bugs.The enjoyment of playing this game is only matched by the multitude of bugs that you will encounter.Within one night, I have had unlocked characters dissapear 3 times due to the game crashing.I have experienced monsters showing up on one players screen but not another (meanwhile there are objective that require all monsters to be slain to complete the level) This means you are unable to complete the level if your teammates are dead yet are the only ones who can see the monsters. I have seen invincible monsters, teleporting monsters (the connection between players in RoR is poorly implemented). I have played countless games with said person, in which connection speed is stellar. Additionally, we both openned ports, and made sure firewall was not blocking.I have experienced falling through the levels, invisible walls, areas that disable your jump. Additionally, I have seen chests(while using the artifact that makes item drops not random) become locked for the player that uses a special key item - only teammates can open the items.If you really unlucky, you will encounter a bug that progressively uses up memory until you run into a ""Out of memory"" warning. This will promptly close the game, making you lose all progress(including unlocked characters).However, most annoying is the ability for RoR to freeze up most of your components if a crash occurs. Alt-tab no longer works, and using ctrl-alt-delete to bring up the task manager doesn't work either, since Risk of rain does failts to then properly alt tab.  (This may be an issue with Windows 8 and Game Maker, however I do not know enough about how GameMaker ports games over to Windows and if it is the true culrpit) I ended up having to sign out of my profile to get the operating system to automatically close any open programs.This game has a lot of potential, but as of now, it is definitely not worth getting for full price, let alone 25% off. If it goes on sale for 50%+, grab it. But as of now, it just has too many bugs that truly hinder the user experience to warrant buying for anything more."
