,Not Recommended,248820,9074597,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,Mr. Wallet,"This game has an extreme problem with lack of conveyance, which is compounded by its tendency to put you completely at the mercy of the random number generator. I couldn't tell what I was doing wrong or what I was supposed to be doing until my 4th game, which was the same as the first three except stupid-easy instead of impossible.By ""lack of conveyance,"" I mean you don't have any clear idea what you're doing or what your goal is. When your goal seems to be too difficult, there's no indication of what you're doing wrong or how you might be able to modify your strategy to make it easier. Levelling up makes you stronger, but the longer you play the harder it gets. Do you go for the boss immediately or level up first? (It took me an hour to figure out: it's about the same either way.) The game is loaded with anti-patterns like this.(Incidentally, the ideal strategy seems to be to clear out the items in the level, and if the items aren't good enough, just abort and restart and hope for a better set next time so you don't waste your time. Are you having fun yet?)The controls are also extremely stiff, making gameplay very unsatisfying even when you do well. My biggest complaint is that right/left + up didn't work while jumping, making hitting the ladders in midair extremely hard since they have snap-on widths that are too small, but in general it seems like the player characters and monsters were designed in a vaccuum.This game is not well-designed, not well-presented, and not fun. If you want a game in this genre, get Rogue Legacy, which is remarkably close in mechanics but does everything right that this one does wrong."
