,Not Recommended,248820,23354390,"Posted: 2 June, 2016",all,Cinaxis,"Before you slide past my non-reccomendation of this game, hear me out.From an asthetic viewpoint, the game is fine if not optimal. It runs well on my laptop alone. The graphics have a nice retro feel, and the environment is interesting.HOWEVER, the gameplay is the lack-luster. Not because it isn't interactive, but because the control scheme is simply too much for me to bear. The inital button set up is: Movement through arrows. Jump with space. Fairly standard. But essential components such as your attacks (which vary with each character) are the X, C, V, and, B keys.Now of course you can change these out through the options but honestly, in my own opinion, theres no natural way to set up the controls.Also, the controller support is spotty at best. (I do use an Afterglow controller, so it may be due to some type of issue with the controller itself, and not the game)Is it a bad game? I don't think so. It has a LOT of potential to be amazing in its own right. I simply dont think it's worth the asking price. Not to mention it hasn't seen an update or likely and Dev insight in a long, long time."
