,Recommended,248820,21650738,"Posted: 5 March, 2016",all,Metro Retro | gamekit.com,"Basic InformationTitle: Risk of RainGenre: Action, Indie, RPGDeveloper: Hopoo Games, LLCPublisher: ChucklefishRelease Date: 8 Nov, 2013OverviewRisk Of Rain is a Rogue-like, difficult game with 2D pixelated graphics, and definatly in my top 10 games on steam. The game itself is pretty solid and provides a ton of replay value. It has some RNG in the game which adds to the replay value of the game itself. It has Multiplayer which is really fun when you have a few buddies to help you through the game.Game PlayRisk Of Rain is a Rogue-like game, which means that you know this game isn't going to be easy. It has perma-death and survival elements in the game that really make the game what it is. When you first start off playing this game you might die, A lot. You will not complete this game in you're first few runs. You are going to need to learn and adapt to your situations and how you're going to survive this. The game is really fun, even though you might die a lot and get fustrated you'll want to come back to it and play 'one' more time. The basic of what you have to do is to find the portal, activate it and then survive until you kill all the enmies on the area then teleport to the next area. As 'easy' as this sounds it's really not. You are kind of up against a timer in some aspects, the longer you are staying in the area the harder it'll get. But why would you stay in the area and not go straight to the portal? Well to collect items you need to open chests, to open chests you need enough money, to get money you need to kill enemies, to kill enemies you have to wait until they spawn. So the process forces you to stay in a area to get the items that are in the chest. A really coll mechanic if you ask me. The game has a nice variety of characters and powerups that you collect on you're journey. Other collectable include secret artifacts that you can use to modify you're game to make it a bit different. For example one of the artifacts will called Glass does the following: Deal 500% damage, but have 10% health. There are 9 others and you can put these into you're runs if you want to variey you're gaming experience with this game. This adds replay value and makes this game really enjoyable. There are a few glitches that I have encountered while playing the game, such as when you start a new run you will just continously fall through the world, and sometimes the enemies would freeze and you can't kill them or do anything.Score (Out Of 10): 9 - Besides a few minor bugs the game is superb! Really high replay value and some really interesting collectable to keep you playing more and more.Graphics/art styleThe game itself really has done well with the pixelated graphics, Especially all the animations of the characters and their own personal abilities that they have. That along with the huge amount of enemies that you encounter throughout playing a few runs is really impressive. Some of the bosses are really well animated with their attacks as well. Everything just really seems to fit in with this sort of game play that this game has to offer. It doesn't seem lazy with the animations that some games have, it really seems that the developers put a lot of effort in the animtations and general art style of this game.Score (Out Of 10): 10 - Beautifully done pixel graphics with some really nice animations from the characters you play to the enemies that you defeat.Music & SoundThe music and the soudns kind of bring this game down a little bit. The sounds are a bit generic for my taste and the music isn't really all that it could be. If the game could add some more music and some more variation then I would really like to hear that. Otherwise for the time being I will be listening to my own music while playing this game.Score (Out Of 10): 5 - Could have a bit more music variation and not as generic sounds.ConclusionThis game is really fun. If you can see past some of the generic sounds and repeptitive music of the game then it is really fun. The graphics for this game are superb, and the animtations are in no way 'lazy.' Each character and enemie have their own custom animations. It also has a high replay value which is wha you want in these difficult, perma-death rogue-like games. Really fun with friends or playing solo!For more reviews on a wide range of games, go and followGood Games Giveaways & Reviewscurator grouphere."
