76561198068089599,Not Recommended,248820,34162452,Posted: 10 August,all,The Voiceless,"I played this game at launch and recently got back into it. The game looks fantastic and the soundtrack is stellar.The problem, however, is that the game is ludicrously unbalanced in almost every aspect of combat. The only way to survive here is to be constantly running away from enemies and turn around to fire one shot at them, then run away again. This is boring as♥♥♥♥♥♥and most enemies can even run as fast as you can, meaning there isn't a single point where you can reliably get a hit on enemies. Melee characters are objectively worse than ranged ones because of this.Having infintely respawning enemies once you activate the boss is one of the worst design decisions I've ever seen. You're told to run away until time runs out, but there's two problems with this. One, it means you have to constantly dodge the boss for 90 seconds while ensuring you get no progress since enemies respawn infinitely and there's no opportunity to attack the boss. This is a pointless time waste as far as I'm concerned. Two, once the smoke clears and the boss is dead, the remaining enemies are sometimes clumped into a swarm on one platform. I legitimately don't understand what the developers expect you to do in that situation. If you're a melee character, you have to restart. If you have a ranged attack, you literally either have to jump onto the platform, fire once, and jump out lest you get overrun immediately, or you have to exploit the enemies' inability to move from the platform and just shoot from safety. This doesn't work on later stages, though, since you'll have an absurd amount of enemies that can teleport and fly while you're stuck running away forever until you die from getting hit from nowhere.The only way to get past this is by getting lucky on some trinket spawns. Some of these make you so overpowered that the game turns into ""quit when you get bored"" instead of the normal ""quit because you can't even attack things"".I really want this game to be good, but I can't in good conscience recommend this. It's so bad it's like they didn't even play test it."
