,Not Recommended,248820,34195283,Posted: 12 August,all,Hello BEAR,"It is with heavy heart that I cannot recommend this game.I do like Risk of Rain, as should be obvious by how much I've played it. It does have some curious balance decisions that are a bit frustrating, but ultimately forgivable.What's not forgivable are the bugs. I am on Linux and about one in every four games I play ends in a crash. I have scoured the internet, tried dozens of fixes, and I still get errors about missing Game Objects. This happens across two different computers running Ubuntu, and even on my windows machine the game has crashed on me a few times. The final straw is the fact that I cannot even unlock the miner because the game crashes every time the boss to unlock him spawns.A few small things that would at least help mitigate the worst of the trouble would be making cloud saving a thing, and also making it so when you unlock something the unlock is instantly recorded into your save file, not at the end of the run. I don't know if this would be enough to make me want to play again but it would be a major step in the right direction.It's too bad because without the bugs this would be an easy recommend, the art is great, the soundtrack is good, gameplay is overall dynamic and interesting, but with this many game breaking bugs I can't even enjoy it anymore."
