,Not Recommended,248820,7880025,"Posted: 2 December, 2013",all,lufia22,"My recommendation is 'No' unless you've played all the other roguelikes out there, as I would recomment those first. RoR is fun, but I don't think it will stick with me and I already find myself tiring of it. RoR is lacking in both the strategy/planning aspect that you might get from a game like FTL and the skill aspect that you might get in a game like Spelunky. Much like Binding of Isaac, your success can heavily vary depending on which items you get, but unlike Isaac, there doesn't feel like as much skill is involved. The main strategy seems to be to kite left or right. There doesn't seem to be too many projectiles to dodge and you can always just run from a fight. I highly recommend Rogue Legacy over this if you want a side-scrolling roguelike. Rogue Legacy feels far more skill intensive. Risk of Rain feels more like the items play the game for you. Either you get lucky and feel massively overpowered or you don't, and you struggle."
