,Not Recommended,248820,25350179,"Posted: 4 September, 2016",all,engie,"After first 5 hours it feels like you are playing a flash game. Thanks to the way the game spawns enemies - the longer you play the faster they spawn. + Their health gets bigger and bigger.""The longer you play - the harder it gets"" says teaser video. So it gets advertised. The cheap enemy implementation.XInput only- I have 2 no-brand Direct Input gamepads and none of them work, but they ARE working with ""x360ce"" (v.2.0.2 tested) (it is XInput emulator). And in ""System Requirements"" it says ""Microsoft Xbox 360 Controller orDirect Input compatible controller"" so this is a lie.Oh... so you will just use x360ce as a solution then? OK. Let's play coop with a friend that HAS x360 gamepad. Damn it, when I use x360ce MINE Direct Input gamepad works but HIS x360 gamepad not. And vice versa without x360ce. ->""Fu** it. Let's play something else""Crash. Very crash.Makes you wonder if the developers even tested their own game. Becausewhen you get buffed enough to survive, you start to worry LESS about surviving and MORE about crashing the game.(You can expect this if you are playing your match for a 1+ hour - with a ton of buffs of course.) And you start to make a note of a powerful buffs that crashed the game, so that you will AVOID them next time like a plague.My game crashed 3 times in 10 hours: 2 of them the whole PC was bricked and I had to pull the plug.How to crash your game (tutorial):Choose engineer and activate the ""Command"" artifact. Pickup a bunch of buffs that increase attack power, like ""Brilliant Behemoth"" (+20% explosion damage) and ""Ceremonial Dagger"" (Fire two additional bolts). Then a bunch of buffs that automatically deal additional attacks on enemy's death. Pickup a bunch of other buffs that suit your taste.Play for 60+ minutes, get ton of buffs - as much as you can with priority to those mentioned above.Stand somewhere on a rope/stairs for the entire level so that the enemy will keep spawning near you, in the same spots. (You will have to move up/down on a rope a bit to avoid homing rockets.)When they all spawned - move around and keep spamming ""Thermal harpoon"" to finish them of remotely (more safe). At some point when one of them dies it will set a chain reaction for the whole pack, because each death will damage others, and they will die and damage others, etc.- ???-Risk of Crash.There are plenty of ways to crash but this one is more reliable. BUT this is also a way to SURVIVE and play the game, so it makes the game harder to play. And all becauseyou are fighting a crappy game optimization - not the enemies. Let's play a game called ""Lets keep looking at dropping FPS nervously"".Often I was forced to memorize the patterns of buffs that crashed the game and then restart the game with never getting too many of those (powerful) buffs, simply because they often crashed the game.So tell me, how I'm supposed to play a game like this?Yes, I know. There are plenty of characters/buffs/artifacts to unlock. I unlocked most of them. But none of that amends all mentioned above.TLDR:If you liked what you saw in teaser video. If you have Xbox 360 gamepad and don't mind game crashing because of a too many stacked buffs (and don't mind this never being fixed) then go ahead and buy this game.Aside from game crashes that I'm experiencing with long plays: the game is OK. But it's monotonous and gets old quickly, and 'XInput only' limits the 2 player co-cop playability."
