76561198352634058,Not Recommended,248820,33940501,Posted: 31 July,all,Bagalagalaga,Join your noble 8 pixel blob on a quest to shoot squares at colorful shapes. The colorful shapes take a hell of a lot of squares to defeat though so it gets a bit tedious.
,Not Recommended,248820,11169332,"Posted: 10 July, 2014",all,M⌬rtius,"How can I describe this game in two words? Kiting simulator. There's a huge variation of classes but with most of them you will be running around fleeing from your enemies while using a few skills here and there, the exception is the enforcer and the sniper which sort of don't fit into the games huge amount of tanky and damage absorbing mobs which deal more damage the more time you spend in the game.Many people will tell you that the best tactic for going through levels is to spend as little time in the levels as possible but this is absurdly impossible because you will spend around 2-3 minutes looking for the teleporter and then you will have about a few minutes left until the next difficulty to deal with the boss, this is of course on the normal difficulty not hard so you can see just how unbalanced the game is. Unfortunatly the developer decided to add a 90 second timer and the mobs during these 90 seconds infinatly spawn so good luck with that... In my opinion this is a stupid design decision because if you do try to kill the boss with the mobs spawning around you there are more chances of you dying but you breeze through the level faster whereas if you try to kite for the 90 seconds and then kill the mobs after those 90 seconds are past you will spend more time in the level and ultimatly the difficulty gets harder, either way you're going to have to kill both the boss and the enemies that are left when the 90 second timer is over. This is where it fundamentally broken there isn't a middle ground it seems that all you do results in a harder difficulty for you and I understand that rogue like games do have a lot of risk behind them but players do need some sort of comprimise, you can't give the player multiple ways of tackling a problem when the end result is still the same because then the player will become fustrated and helpless.The problems with the game does not just stop there. With the artifact Command which you will find by playing through the game you have the option to choose any item from a tier, this includes chests and random items (items that have a ? on them), it drops a little box and you can choose the item you want. The problem with this artifact lies within the shrines, as you throw your money at the shrine you get the random item with the help of the artifact, the key or button used to pay the shrines is the same as the key to choose an item from the box that just dropped, this means that you will end up accidently paying your money towards the shrine 2-3x more depending on how much money you have left and how many boxes drop. This is a major annoyance for me because at times I ran out of money because I ended up throwing paying the rest of my money to the shrines even though I did not want to. The developer really messed up with the artifact and I doubt he is going to read my review and patch it but if he does then that would be great.Lastly... And this a problem that has caused me the loss of games when it wasn't my fault and rather the developer who failed to test this through properly or simply ignored the problem. When opening the boxes that you get with the artifact Command you have to select the item in REAL TIME, this means that when you're selecting an item from the box you will most likely end up getting chewed up if you do not select it quickly. There should be some sort of pause so that the player can choose the item without having to panick about getting killed, I cannot tell you how many times I have died due to this, you may say ""just wait until you kill the mobs and then come back"" if I activate the boxes during the boss timer then I face the threat of infinite spawning mobs and I'd have to leave the location and then return which would waste my time, didn't the developer even consider the fact that this would make the artifact annoying to players?All that I said sums up how the game feels to me, it feels unabalanced and broken. Sure its a good timewaster and don't get me wrong I did enjoy the game but I felt far more fustrated and annoyed and I play my games to have fun and release stress not create stress. Thank you for taking the time to read this review, it was fairly short but I didn't want to spoil any of the classes by going too indepth.One last note. I know that swarms of angry Risk of Rain fans are going to come swarming towards me since that is how Steam works, if a games mostly positive and you say anything negative about it you will get showered by hate and downvotes but before you do that please accept the fact that this is from my perspective, if you cannot accept it then you're too shallow. I won't be arguing with someone that is throwing around arguments with a primitive attitude."
