76561198001379620,Recommended,248820,10671217,"Posted: 22 June, 2014",all,Jargoseth,"I just got this on the sale and i can say, i couldn't be happier with how this little gem turned out.The art-style is really cool with it's smooth pixelated visuals, and the gameplay is just plain awesome.You know that thing that everyone keeps going on about in their games, that ""no two playthroughs will ever be the same""?Well it actually applies here with that feeling being conveyed not only by the randomised environments, but with the fundamental way the gameplay plays out.You have your 4 skills that do something depending on your character and then while exploring you come across chests and totems and stuff like that, that you spend money on for weapons and items that actually stack all together on your character.So you might end up having a guy with a chance to fire rockets per hit,a mortar shell being fired per hit, chance of setting your enemies on fire when getting the kill, and making the burst when you take them out, damaging fellow opponents.Basicly the ""a gun that fires guns"" comes into full effect, offering a spectacle unlike i have ever seen, and with 4 player net or local co-op, this is just my cup of tea.Masterpiece that should not be missed."
