,Recommended,248820,10347609,"Posted: 4 June, 2014",all,EpicTanooki,"As you're piloting your cargo ship, the UES Contact Light, everything is going fine. You, along with your crew, some stowaways, an exotic animal, and the robot janitor, are going about your days, delivering packages across the cosmos. Suddenly, you lose all power, but the alarm sirens buzz off, running off the spare power. You search around, hoping to fing the intruders, suddenly, a kingly figures appears before a crowd of the planet's inhabitants, you start to pull out your gun, but the man flings you into a pod, and sends you towards your certain demise. You survive the crash, but your suit is damaged, and your crew is lost, leaving you, armed with a gun, your wits, and whatever you can scavenge from your ships cargo containers, you are forced to jump around the planet, teleporter to teleporter, to face ""Providence,"" as you've come to call the kingly figure, and reclaim your ship, honor, and crew.Risk of Rain is easily worth $10 dollars, if you have spare free time, enjoy rogue-likes, or are looking for a unique experience. This game will very easily hold you over, with tons of unlocks, 11 interesting classes, both a single and multiplayer experience, and the newly added artifacts, Risk of Rain holds much more than can be explained. I have put hours into unlocking the unique items, and enjoying the pleasing art and music style. The combat is smooth, the items are interesting, and the game provides a good challenge, but it always feels fair."
