,Recommended,248820,10751542,"Posted: 24 June, 2014",all,ClockTower,"This is a great game and is very fun solo or with friends but there are a few flaws: First I picked this game up in he comunity's choice sale and it was advertised as co-op. While this is technicaly true it requires port forwarding and for you to give you own router ip adress to the people joining your game, so make sure you trust them. Also from what I can see there is no random join match, which may be important to you; not so much for me. One other thing is that I don't know if it is just the randomness of the game or my good luck, but I completed the game on my third try. This isn't a downside however because the game has infinite replayability, but there is a harder difficulty so I might have to play on that ; ). One final thing is that the levels do not seem to be randomly generated. There are subtle changes but it is possible to remember where you are going in all the different enviroments. The teleporter placement does change though which can often catch you off guard and be your undoing. Overall this is a brilliant game and i can see myself spending well over 10 or maybe 20 hours on this game which i would say is a very resonable for the price. Oh and just as a last note  I haven't encoutered any frame drop, but there are multiple reports of it so be aware."
