,Recommended,248820,8300555,"Posted: 26 December, 2013",all,Cevo,"Would recommend this (and have) to anyone looking for a decent rogue-like experience. The game starts out ridiculously difficult. Some people kick off tearing through it like tissue paper, but the majority struggle with just the first level.. but that's okay, that's a roguelike for you. It's a clean 50/50 between luck and skill, so ignore anyone who goes on about being a natural. It's possible to get a spree of crappy items, dooming you as you progress to enemies that take chunks of your life.There's built in controller support that I personally LOVE to use and abuse, I play with my controller often, it's a natural experience and it even opens up splitscreen multiplayer capabilities, which is most enjoyable. Online multiplayer is great too, and even with my distance lag being in Japan I can enjoy playing with randoms all over the world, the net code does it's job and makes the game very enjoyable.There's a plethora of characters to unlock and each offers a unique and enjoyable experience. Some are more suited for multiplayer, the sniper is great solo but is an ultimate boss killer when your allies keep the baddies off of you.I've gotten more than my money's worth from this game and encourage anyone to play it. 16 hours well spent!"
