,Recommended,248820,11139822,"Posted: 8 July, 2014",all,A Penguin,"You could do a lot worse for tenbux. This game rewards skillful play, and the mechanics may be frustrating if you are looking for a casual platformer.You are one of several characters with a unique 4-set of powers. Look through the level for the teleporter, activate it, face a swarm of enemies, kill them all, and his the tele to get to the next level. There is a final level and boss fight, and then the game ends -- or you can choose to loop through the levels again with increased difficulty until you die or decide to go to the last level. Difficulty increases with time, so the longer you linger, the harder the enemies become. You get stronger by levelling up  by defeating enemies and by finding power-ups that allow you to do more damage per second (or let you move faster, jump higher, etc). You also get stronger by gaining skill with the character. Yes, your skill does factor into the balance of power.The power-ups are easily the biggest hang-up about the gamer: they are mostly random. Some power-ups are more desirable than others. If you neglect to get good at the game, you will have a tough time and will likely be frustrated by random drops. If you want to get good, you will be able to make do with any set of random drops. There is an unlockable option that allows you to select what power-up you get from a randomly-dropped tier which alleviates this problem somewhat.There are many unlockables; this is either good or bad, depending on your opinion about unlockables. The classes are different and each one offers a mostly unique gameplay. The levels are colorful and varied, but there are only so many of them, and depiste being pesudo-random, they do get a little repetitive. Some levels are easier (smaller) than others. The soundtrack is excellent. The game is poorly optimized: later levels will probably cause you to lag. Gameplay is tight and fast with only a little room to breathe. There is a multiplayer mode -- if you can get it to work -- if you're into that kind of thing. Some classes (sniper) depend on your skills more than others (huntress).That's about all there is to say. It's solid in some places, and weak in others. Overall, I liked it, and would recommend this game if you want what it offers. Challenging with a lot to master, but not completely unforgiving."
