,Recommended,248820,11006821,"Posted: 1 July, 2014",all,Marfle-Pop,"Risk of Rain is a roguelike platformer with lots of trial and error, similarly to a game like The Binding of Isaac. It may be extremely tough for you to get a handle on the game early on, but later on in the game it becomes easier once you know enemies patterns, types, abilities, and unlock characters that you can play to your own liking. You can unlock artifacts, which also make the game incredibly fun while also making it somewhat easier, depending on which ones you choose. There are some that harshly reduce your health while giving you a giant damage bonus, and there are some which make only the most powerful types of monsters appear. If I were you, I would definitely play this game with online friends. Playing this game with a friend on the same screen becomes a burden, and sometimes we would argue for items or one of us would fall out of the screen region and we would have to scramble to get the other player on screen. It's a fun but challenging game that you should play on your own monitor for the best experience."
