76561198042757315,Recommended,248820,9228624,"Posted: 22 February, 2014",all,SamuraiCupcake,"Like indy games? This is the best recent example I can think of of a super fun ''old school'' game, more FUN than most triple-A titles out there? Why is that? How is this better than Call of Duty? Simple.First off, I must commend the soundtrack. The music for this is... how can I say this... INCREDIBLE. There's two main ''phases'' to the game : looking for the teleporter to the next level, where the music is more relaxed and you really get to enjoy the melody, then BOSS FIGHTS once you've started the teleporter's countdown, where the music goes totally crazy and badass. For example, the trailer's tune is one of the boss tunes. Truly, kudos mr. Christodoulou, you are one incredible composer.Then there's the graphics. This is a fine example of ''less is more''. The graphics are decidedly retro, using very minimalistic pixel style, but it somehow feels fresh and new as opposed to old and passé. The animation is really well done, flashy and fluid. The monsters you fight are all really creatively designed and have varied attacks, sizes and strenght. Your own character is super small, but! this intentional to create the illusion of scale when facing bosses. They seem HUGE because of this, it is a very effective technique. The levels are nice and varied, but a bit too big and take a looooong time to get across, which can get tiresome when you're looking for the exit. Thankfully, there's plenty of detail, bonuses and spawning enemies to keep you invested. Oh, and the colors. The game uses a very nice palette of colors, which is perhaps an understatement. Just look at the screenshots, haha : the main color here is dark blue/purple, so colors like the bright orange of your tiny character REALLY pop!But really, you'll get into it thanks to the fun gameplay! Where to start... you might be a little lost when you start the game. This is good! Your character is lost, so this feeling of mystery is appropriate! You simply explore the vast levels and combat spawning enemies to survive. YES! This is a survival game. Not survival horror, but survival ACTION! You'll be spending the majority of the time running away from HORDES of enemies, using your array of 4 abilities to take them out one by one. You start with one class, the commando, but through progressing... and finding secrets... you'll unlock the other survivors, each with their own unique gameplay style. Similar to games like League of Legends, you have the choice between a close-range damage-over-time character, or a long-range instant-kill sniper, each with their pros and cons. Its actually HARDER when you choose a new class, but its still a hell of a lot of fun to master them all.I didn't really play multiplayer, mostly because none of my friends got this game, and keep in mind that there's no lobby listing : you need to give someone a IP for them to join or vice versa. I'm sure its awesome though, as many classes, like the shield-bearing Enforcer seem useful for teamwork.Unfortunatly... there's not really much of a story. From what I pieced together, you're on a transport ship carrying all sorts of items across the galaxy, when your cargo gets attacked by a mysterious character. All the loot goes flying down to the planet below, as with your escape pod. Your goal is, obviously, to survive on the planet populated by exclusively hostile life, scavenging the cargo that fell to give yourself an advantage. Aside from that, find the other survivors and, hopefully, get back to the ship and escape the planet. That's... pretty much it. It works. A detailed narrative would of simply distracted the player from the gameplay.So yeah! If you're already a fan of platformers like Cave Story or Metroid, this a no-brainer : you'll love this like I loved this. You'll love this to bits, flaming, meaty bits of your own blasted corpse. Because be warned, this game is HARD.VERY HARD!!! AND VERY ADDICTING!!!But incredibly fun! :)Its only flaw that really bothered me was the lenghty traveling through the big flat levels, but those moments were few and far between, as enemies keep popping left and right.An absolute romp. A bit short if you just get to the ending on easy, but it will take MANY replays to get through on the harder difficulties. As the description states, the game gets harder to longer you play, so be quick!9/10"
