76561198092187479,Recommended,248820,7733542,"Posted: 24 November, 2013",all,3dRes,"A fantastic roguelike game where its punishment is both rewarding, and satisfying. The progression system is just like any other roguelike game; unlock characters and gain items throughout different playthroughs.Risk of Rain offers 9 very different, but unique playable characters. They each have a set of 4 abilities (think MOBA: Dota 2 or Smite) and these can be used to kill and progress. There is also the collectible items such as Monster Logs. These are dropped by each enemy and provide a damage bonus on them when picked up. 15 of these also unlocks the chracter 'Huntres'. The items that are used in every run really offer different ways to kill or escape. The only problem i have with the item pickups is that most have no real description which tells its use e.g. the Ukulele says ""his music was electric"" which doesn't suggest much about the item.The common approach set by most roguelike games, ""just one more run"", really utilizes the enjoyment and replayabilitiy that Risk of Rain has to offer. I have always been put off by this genre because it feels more repetitive by each game brought out. That experience is not served within RoR which is why i highly recommend the game.8.5/10"
