,Recommended,248820,9073139,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,Dopey,"A rogue-like and platformer stepchild, with randomized enemies, platformer gameplay, though all the maps are not procedural so each map is exactly the same, though there are a few alternatives for each tier. Game difficulty increases as time goes by, with higher difficulties reducing the time it takes for the difficulty to go up and is shown by a bar that slowly fills on the top right next to the time. Items are random, and enemy spawns for the most part are random. You must find a portal and use it to get a timer to survive, it spawns heavy amounts of units and a boss when activated and if you survive the time, no more enemies spawn and you must clear the level of all enemies before you can progress. When you go to a new level it resets your coins to 0 so make sure you use them all buying automaated drones that support or damage, opening chests, buying an item from a shop that disappears after you buy 1 item. Even shrines that you pay tribute in health or coins to for a chance at an item. There are several classes to play, yoou only start with one and must unlock the rest but the starting one is a great choice for beating the game the first time around. It has co-op but i heard its buggy and have not tried it myself. Overall a great roguelike in the world of platformers which keeps you playing to get one step further."
