,Recommended,248820,9074512,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,Ignitehawk,"It's a lot of fun to play, especially when you figure out the tricks to each character, and acquiring tons of items in order to go from teeny weakling to godly force is immensely satisfying. Add to this unlockable items, classes, and cool monster logs to collect, and you've got yourself a game that gives you lots of reason to keep playing.That said, the game still has its cons. The first is that some classes have distinctly greater survival rates than others. The Commando (which you start with) will always be one of the best classes, and some of the harder classes to unlock (which you expect to be awesome) are disappointingly underpowered. The other con is that the action, while frenzied and fun, doesn't have a whole lot of depth to it; sure, enemies attack differently, but most attacks are avoided by running away and jumping repeatedly, which doesn't exactly emphasize skill.Don't let that dissuade you, however - the game's lack of involving combat is replaced by each class's learning curve, and despite some of them being noticably better than others, they're all pretty fun to play.Pick this up, and whether you have companions to battle the hordes beside or not, you'll have a great time."
