,Recommended,248820,9075882,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,Scoli,"REALLY fun in multiplayer. I highly recommend a controller, though several of my friends played just fine on keyboard. Several different classes makes for unique combinations of teams, and each class can utilize certain items better than others. The achievements are fun to hunt after, though it gets boring once you unlock everything. Granted the game is still fun, but you lose that sense of.. challenge? Purpose? Apart from trying to beat your own ""high score"" but eh. I still put a decent amount of time into it, especially for a $10 game.As far as ""randomly generated"" goes, it should be procedurally generated. The items locations/availability and drops from monsters are randomized (to an extent), but the overmall map structure is probably 85% the same each time. You just might get extra areas in a map, or extra walls that block certain shortcuts.You just have 2 map choices for the first 3 stages. So you get A or B, then C or D, then E or F, G, H. At G, you can choose to go repeat the first stages, or advance to the final stages. Since difficulty increases with time (up to a cap) you're betting on yourself that you can run all 4 stages again + the last stage + final boss at a higher difficulty (with the chance at items and exp through the stages, of course.)Overall, 7/10. Got bored of it after a while, but I was obsessed with it when playing it."
