,Recommended,248820,9089291,"Posted: 13 February, 2014",all,morang,"Pretty fun, and pretty difficult. If you like games like Binding of Isaac, Spelunky, and Rogue Legacy, you'll probably like this one. It starts out really hard, but as you get better, unlock more characters, and learn the strategies for getting through the levels it becomes a fun challenge.In case it's not fairly obvious from the description, the game is all about combat and survival. The goal of each level is to find the teleporter, activate it, and then kill all the enemies that spawn. Each character has four abilities (if you play League or DotA you can rebind to QWER like I did). One is a basic attack, and the other three are more powerful or useful abilities with short cooldowns (2-10 seconds or so). There's no mana or anything, so you're basically always running around kiting and spamming your abilities. You get items that either give you passive bonuses (lifesteal, bleed damage, dying enemy explosions, etc) or effects that you can activate (boomerang sawblade, deployable mines, instant heal, etc). The classes have very different playstyles; I've only unlocked three so far, but they all have different strategies and ability combos that you need to learn to play them well."
