,Recommended,248820,7987373,"Posted: 9 December, 2013",all,Shademan,"This...game...is..AWESOME!I'm tempted to compare this to a side scrolling sprite version of Binding of Isaac but that wouldn't do it justice. Risk of Rain is by itself an amazing roguelike. The player controls a survivor of an interstellar space transport that has crashed on an inhospitable planet. Using the parcels that were being transported, the player must survive the increasingly difficult trials of the planet and escape back to the ship which is trapped in orbit.Risk of Rain is unique in that it's difficulty increases as time passes, not as the player progresses in levels. This means that the first level could be as hard as the last level depending on how long you spend fighting monsters. In each level the player has to find the teleporter and survive 90 seconds while it powers up before teleporting to the next stage. Of course it's not advisable that the player immediately starts up the teleporter when he finds it. Instead it's imperative that they collect the various powerups scattered throughout the level and gain some levels.The game remains fresh by rewarding players with unlockable items and classes. There are a plethora of items with cool gameplay effects, ranging from increased health regeneration to causing killed enemies to explode into purply bits of dead soul that blow up other enemies. Items are unlocked by completing challenging achievements. Unlike most games though, these achievements happen quite naturally and aren't as far flung as some games.The best part of the game though, and what keeps me coming back, is the classes. Whenever I feel like I'm sick and tired of the game I unlock a new class, and boy are these classes unique! Unlike Binding of Isaac, each character you unlock has their own skillset and combat style that differ vastly from each other. The Commando focuses on dodging fast and shooting enemies from a distance while the test subject Acrid tears into enemies with his poisonous mutant claws.Beyond gameplay, Risk of Rain has a great story that can be gleaned from the various item and monster logs the player collects in their inevitable journey. The accompanying OST is truly beautiful and sometimes I find myself just standing around listening to it as my inevitable doom closes on me.Overall, I definitely recommend Risk of Rain. It's a stylish fast-paced roguelike sidescroller that's well worth it's price tag. Just be prepared to die. Alot."
,Recommended,248820,7677705,"Posted: 16 November, 2013",all,Keith,Tons of fun and well worth the money. If it is ever on sale there is no excuse not to pick this game up.
