,Not Recommended,248820,10854010,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,Cyanure,"I generally like rogue-like game and find some of them to be very enjoyable and addictive (Binding of Isaac, Rogue Legacy, Dungeons of Dredmor, Pixel Dungeon for example). Unfortunately, Risk of Rain is not one of them, it is way too brutal and doesn't do much to keep you interested in playing more.To give an example, an average ennemy will take about 10 regular shots to kill. When you start, with a couple of ennemies you can handle them quite easily, but few minutes later, you will find yourself fighting against a horde of 10-15 ennemies, all running toward you. You might succeed in killing one or two, but after that you'll become overwhelmed quite fast as new ennemies are spawning as you kill them, forcing you to run away and try to avoid ennemies. When you're done with a boss, you still have to kill all remaining ennemies, which can be very hard when 20-30 are all at the same place. 1 to 3 seconds are enough for them to kill you if you don't avoid them.The items that you can buy sometimes gives you a small advantage, but as the difficulty of the game increase the longer you play, the small advantages aren't enough to keep you continuing without getting kill.That being said, I did enjoyed the music and the art direction of the game.For me to recommend this game, two things would need to change: reducing the number of shots needed to kill ennemies (or make different levels of difficulty to please casual and very hardcore gamers) and remove (or make optionnal) the ""gets harder the longer you play"" caracteristic."
