,Recommended,248820,11472559,"Posted: 29 July, 2014",all,BigZman95,"Risk of Rain is a phenominal game and is one of the most enjoyable games I have played in a long time. Playing this game in local co-op is some of THE most fun you can have with your friends. It will make you laugh, cry, sigh in frustration but ulltimately keep you coming back. The game's difficulty ups as time goes on which adds to the intensity. At some of the higher levels bosses almost continually spawn. While the game punishes players it also rewards them highly with upgrades and useable items. Risk of Rain provides a challenge but never becomes unenjoyable. It has a unique vibe to it which feels old school but more modern at the same time. It's hard to tell from the videos and screenshots but it plays mostly like a platformer but you have a main attack which never needs to recharge and three abilities which vary by class that take time to recharge between uses. Having a strategy adds a deeper level of gameplay to an otherwise simple game. You will want a team with a variety of abilities and then use those abilities to compliment eachother. Some of the most fun in this game is figuring tactics to use on the enemies that are so good it almost feels like cheating. Depending on the classes your team chooses, the gameplay will change drastically. It can be anywhere from a more tactical approach to run and gun. Risk of Rain is a fantastic game and is even better with friends. Couch co-op has never been so intense and enjoyable. It will beg you to beat the game over and over again."
