,Recommended,248820,8805245,"Posted: 22 January, 2014",all,Kpiddy,"One clear in, and I'm having the time of my life.Risk of Rain can start out feeling unfair. Enemies seem overpowered, and items can appear useless. The first few games I played felt ridiculously hard.A full game lasts about 40-60 minutes. However, most games end around the 20-30 mark, where the game really tests to see if you've been prioritizing and collecting the right kinds of items. Make sure you've got some time to dedicate to this one. Winning depends on getting in the flow, and learning how to kite and dodge your enemies.Give it a couple goes. After you get a lucky streak of items, I guarentee  you'll be starting again, craving that magical experience where you were breifly allowed to be the hunter, not the hunted.Winning can feel a bit dependant on items, but roulette items, stores, and teired chests help increase predictability. I was always able to get 2 or 3 ""Great"" items per run without much trouble.If you've got a friend, play with them. It's much easier to manage groups when you have some class variaty. Just make sure you don't rob all of their items.The game's a bit rough around the edges. Framerate drops when adding and removing input devices, as mentioned in the readme. The game's last level can be very taxing on systems. However, the core experience is too much fun to give this one a pass. For 10 bucks, I can't say no."
