,Recommended,248820,10649563,"Posted: 21 June, 2014",all,Shiloh,"Risk of Rain, is in my opinion, one of the beast indie rogue likes of the year, if not of all time. It pulls the nearly perfect synergy of random generation and unforgiving no save, one life, one go playstyle of the rogue like genre. The game's system of level progression and mob spawning is unforgiving and difficult, but is insanely addicting. Also the character selection gives a wide variety on different playstyles to fit you in particular, while still keeping the game interesting if you would like the challenge of switching up your particular playstyle. The random generation of chest items and boss items makes each run nearly unidentifiable from the previous. The only quip I have with this astounding game is the lack of random generation in the levels. There are normally 2 different ""terrains"" on each level and each ""terrain"" has about 2-3 different generations. Unfortunatley after your 10th or so time through the game, the level design becomes easily identifiable and stale. Nonetheless, this is still an incredibly addicting, satisfying, and frustatingly difficult game to spend hours on end mastering. 8.5/10"
