76561198039111810,Recommended,248820,9082327,"Posted: 13 February, 2014",all,J-Shox,"This is a truly brilliant game. The constant factors of perma-death, strong starting enemies, and increasing difficulty over time give this game an oddly pleasant and challenging atmosphere. I'm not quite sure how, but it manages to prevent you from raging after losing, unlike a lot of other ""similar"" challenging games. The soundtrack is mind-blowing, to say the least, and I'm not usually a fan of music in games. The time vs. difficulty system is an intelligent design and works far better than I expected. Originally, I thought ""Oh, this is probably gonna end up too difficult for me to even play..."" but somehow, they made it work. The game is both challenging and enjoyable, which is a hard combination to successfully pull off. My ONLY problem with this game is a small one(more of a nit-picky kind of thing). Originally, I thought that the levels were going to be randomly generated... which they are.... kinda. The chests/containers, item-trade, and shrine locations are randomized throughout pre-made levels. I was expecting the TERRAIN to be randomly generated, instead of what populates it... as I said, this is more of a personal, nit-picky thing. HOWEVER, the random generation of features is still more than enough to keep you on your toes and keep things interesting. I HIGHLY suggest this game to most people interested in challenging/semi-challenging, non-raging, kinda-casual(oddly enough), exciting games."
