,Recommended,248820,9050745,"Posted: 10 February, 2014",all,(Mixer.com) Navi Ilivas,"Where do I start with this one... Risk of Rain is a Roguelike with some small RPG elements thrown in there (Leveling up on enemy kills, which boosts stats minorly). This game is very unique in the fact that the longer you stay in a run, the more difficult it gets in scale. Every level you encounter is random, as are the items you can get in a run. There are a total of ten characters in the game, which adds to the replayability, but you have to earn nine of them by playing the game and accomplishing the corresponding in-game achievements.The good: The Replay factor is definitely there, making you want to get that much further than you did before. The Levels are well designed, as are the characters, granted this is an 8-bit game. The scaling difficulty is a very refreshing aspect in the sense of not wanting things too easy as you play.The bad: On older and slower systems, the game lags once you get past Very Hard Difficulty, dropping FPS down to around 15-20 depending on how old your system is. Controller support is a little weird in the sense of skill pushes, but is rather easily grasped once you get a hang of what button does what skill. Some of the items you need to unlock are rather difficult to obtain, especially some of the Character-specific ones (Enforcer, I'm looking at you on this one).Despite the small personal negatives, I would HIGHLY recommend this game to anyone whom is a fan of Roguelikes.As a part of the Attention Deficit Arcade Stream group on Twitch.tv, I give this game a 9/10."
