,Recommended,248820,10583925,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,Guantanamo Bae,"This is the game to buy for Roguelike fans who want a little more action.It combines the randomized levels and items, permanent death, and quick character progression of the roguelike genre with fast paced side-scrolling platformer/shooter mechanics.Like most Roguelikes RoR is short on story, but there are little bits here and there.  The opening showcases a sci-fi space freighter being demolished by a mysterious being, and various bestiary entries that can be found are written from the point of view of the PC which expound on the disastrous inroduction.Gameplay is definitely the showcase in any Roguelike, and Risk of Rain is thoroughly polished in that area.  Featuring 10 different characters each with their own suite of abilities, and an arsenal of 100+ items whose effects range from increasing your basic attack speed to infecting enemies in melee range with a damage over time toxin that jumps on death, replayability is essentially infinite.What makes Risk of Rain unique in the genre is a time system that drives the player forward constantly.  As time passes during gameplay, a meter fills in the upper right corner of the screen increasing the difficulty at certain points.  A player must balance time spent hunting for experience and items in each level with finishing it early before the next stage spawns insurmountable hordes of enemies, providing a tense atmosphere during each playthrough.Risk of Rain also boasts an excellent pixel art style, with expressive animations and distinct enemy outlines so the player can tell at a glance what they are facing.  A color-coded elite spawn system also mixes things up, also allowing instant recognition of immediate threats.The soundtrack is probably the most impressive aspect of the game, with a general exploration theme and boss theme for each level.  It is at once atmospheric and blood pumping, and should be left on when playing.Lastly, Risk of Rain also features online cooperative play, which can provide entire worlds of fun for a group of friends with a night to spare.All in all, Risk of Rain is a real gem and if you enjoy Roguelikes, platformers, or side-scrolling shooters it really should be a part of your Steam library."
,Recommended,248820,10584867,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,Eyzlahn,Another awesome indie game! Love the music and the art! Has my vote.
