,Recommended,248820,13412236,"Posted: 16 December, 2014",all,EarthquakePancake,"Risk of Rain, simply put, is a sci-fi action-adventure rogue-like game.Risk of Rain, specifically put, is the most amazing badass side-scrolling sci-fi shooter I have ever seen. It has more content than almost any other rogue-like game I've ever seen, and is close to perfection in every way.Pros:-Around 15 different classes to choose from, each with their own upsides and downsides to get used to.-Dozens of different items to collect, each giving you specific passive boosts or qualities to add a little quality to what will almost always be your short life.-A great many activated items, which can do anything from launching missiles to placing a torch that fears and damages enemies to even sacrificing a small portion of your health to instantly kill the closest enemy to you (yes, that includes BOSSES).-Several different environments, all with their own unique layouts.-A very uniquely challenging aspect: as time forges on, so does the difficulty. In other words, the longer you live, the less likely you are to continue living.-Although not many, there are a few story elements, such as item and monster logs to show you what you're dealing with.Cons:-Even the easiest difficulty is very challenging for new players. It took me around 5 games to get used to it enough to get past the 2nd stage.-You begin with only the Commando class, which most players consider the worst class in the game. It also can take quite a lot of effort and skill to unlock some of the characters.-Monsters have a tendency to spawn very frequently once you reach around the 6-minute mark.-You must activate a teleporter to transition between levels, and during this time, monsters spawn much more often than they already do, and a powerful boss spawns to make it an even greater challenge to live.-Pressing Ctrl+Esc in the middle of the game will hide it as normal, but there isn't always something in the taskbar for you to click to pull it back up. Even in windowed mode, the taskbar shows no signs of the game being open. If this happens, it also becomes impossible to reopen it with Steam without restarting the computer, as it will bring up a window saying the ""app is already running"". (NOTE: Even if this happens, it may randomly add itself to the taskbar, allowing you to re-enter the game and resume play as normal. However I am not sure of what causes this to happen.)-Exiting a current run brings it to an end instead of saving progress, just as if you had died.In my belief, however, the ups heavily outweigh the downs. This game is obscenely fun and difficult to stop playing once you've started.9/10P.S. The Commando class is actually a good one to have to start out with. He is capable of hitting enemies on the edge of the screen with ease, and his attacks can knock back most enemies, keeping them at bay temporarily. He also has a dodge roll that grants him immunity to all damage until he completes the roll. Overall, he can be very easy to get used to, and getting a lot of items that apply on-hit effects can be ridiculous on him."
,Recommended,248820,13413377,"Posted: 17 December, 2014",all,"Arthur ""Two-Sheds"" Jackson","The first time I played Risk of Rain, I thought it seemed decently fun, although hard, and I didn't touch it for a bit. Later I picked it up again for whatever reason, and saw it's true potential. This is most definitely one of my favorite games, and i couldn't recommend it enough.Very pleasing art style and a really kick♥♥♥♥♥soundtrack make the game aesthetically top notch. A good selection of playable characters, a huge amount of play modifying items, and unlockable ""artifacts"" that change the way the game works. Random enemies and items, as well as semi-random levels give limitless replayability, and tons of unlockables to motivate further. Local and online co-op with up to four friends, (more if you edit a game file), really make the game shine.Outside of the occasional minor glitch, which show up less and less as the devs continue to update, the only problem I've had with Risk of Rain is the wonky direct connect method the online co-op, which is easily remedied with Hamachi, or a similar tunnel service.All in all, I highly recommend Risk of Rain"
