,Recommended,248820,13799407,"Posted: 2 January, 2015",all,EverythingBagel,"This game is deceptively impossible and endlessly fun.Risk of rain gets a whole bunch of things right. It takes the same addictive qualities of Flappy Bird, being that each game starts from level one with no powerups and only 15 coins. You earn coins and EXP by killing enemies, which you can later turn in for power ups, drones that follow you and help you fight, or keep till the end of each level to exchange for EXP. But the deceptive part of this game is that it gets more difficult as time goes on. Every decision you make effects how long it will take you to beat certain levels. Rather than making it through the levels, this game is more about how long you can last.To be honest, I didn't expect much of Risk of Rain when I bought it. I got the four pack while it was on sale and gave it to three of my friends, and we've all been playing it non stop. It's the most frustrating game I've played in a while but it's also probably the most fun. Buy it, even if it's full price. You won't regret it."
