,Recommended,248820,14598406,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,Storm™,"For all you hardcore gaming fans who like to kill endless waves of monsters with tons of powerups to help you along the way, this game is for you.Risk of Rain is a well-constructed survival game with great music, intresting monsters, and nice-looking settings. The characters you play as are also unique in their own way. Each character has different skills; no two are the same. With the dodge roll of the Commando; to the ""Protect and Serve"" skill with the enforcer, which gives you faster firing speed and blocking all attacks from the front, but slows you down, all skills can work in different situations.Another nice concept of ROR is that it gets harder the longer you play. This pressures you into always moving and finding the teleporter and not just trying to find items. Yes, items help you move along easier, but wasting too much time trying to find some, and the game will punish you by amping up the health, attack power, and defense of the monsters that spawn. Farthest I've gotten is to Impossible difficulty.Whether you're a casual gamer or hardcore gamer and like seeing pixel graphics with intense music, Risk of Rain will surely put your skills to the test. Not just by the sheer number of monsters, but by planning out how you'll use your skills, since it's a MUST to use all of them. Risk of Rain is a fantastic and addictive game, that everyone should play."
76561198030692191,Recommended,248820,14598414,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,spasmodik,"Fun game with rogue-like elements. Beware of the crashes when leaving game idle =(Blast aliens and collect items to make yourself more powerful, and eventually the miniboss for each level. The random element with not knowing if you'll pickup powerful items or ""slightly less useful"" items will keep reruns feeling fairly fresh. Eventually you'll unlock other characters for different playstyle, as well as items or artifacts. There is a built-in timer increasing difficulty, and while I'm not a fan of too much stress when playing, this works well with the game while not detracting from it.If you lose interest after the first five minutes, thinking it wasn't for you, try sticking it out a few lives/levels more or playing on easier difficulty to make headway."
