,Recommended,248820,15864471,"Posted: 16 May, 2015",all,BOT C'thulu,"This is an addictive game for having such a simple premise.  Spawn on a planet, clear the stage, gather loot, and continue on.  Each time you play, you select a character with specific skill sets (think MOBA).  Each of the characters feels quite unique and really helps to increase the gameplay.  The game stays fast-paced, especially since the longer you play the more dangerous the enemies become.There are some quirks, though.  The game lets you zoom out to see more of the screen, to the point where the pixel art is 1:1 (your character becomes like 16 pixels tall on the screen).  The GUI and all menus also zoom out, which is unnecessary.  The game loses some of its appeal when zoomed out that much, and you don't feel like you're in as much danger when you can see things coming.  So just don't play zoomed out like that, right?  You get such an advantage in the game while zoomed out that the game just becomes unnecessarily more difficult (and sometimes annoying with faster or long-ranged enemies).Like others, I also had a game breaking bug twice where your character eternally falls through the world.  Thankfully this rarely happens, and only at the beginning of a run (so all you have to do is restart).It's definitely worth playing, though; especially for the price."
