,Recommended,248820,15663142,"Posted: 2 May, 2015",all,armed and autistic,"STORYRisk of Rain is a game where you are stuck on a planet due to a a space ship crash thing. After a series of unfortunate events the ship (specifically is ""Space Train"") crashed and all the ""cargo"" on it escaped. This ""cargo"" happens to consist of dangerous weaponry and viscous animals. You play as a survivor of the crash and you are stuck on a planet with all the other animals and some native animals. This game is really deep too....SOUNDTRACKThis soundtrack is to amazing it needs its own section of the review. The soundtrack feels empowering at times. But at the same time it can sound depressing and can paint a picture in your mind of desolation and hopelessness. The soundtrack really makes the mood for a game that says things like ""Your family will never know how you died"" if you die. Because of that, this game is depressingly badass.GAMEPLAYThis game seems like a side scrolling Borderlands, You murder stuff, loot stuff, and be a badass. There is a HUGE amount of enemies you fight, and each enemy has a chance to to drop a journal entry-like thing. You collect a power ups and relics to help you slaughter animals. So, there's two types of power ups/items Passive items (which will help you the most) and Usable items (these items need to be used, as their name implies)."
