,Recommended,248820,13965545,"Posted: 12 January, 2015",all,Dracohir,"This is one of my first reviews, only my 2nd one in fact, which surprise surprise, it's on another rogue-like game.At first, I did not have high hopes for this game. After getting the game and playing it for a while however, I couldn't really put it down. I did finally get bored however from some bugs like falling through the world constantly, but this usually only happened on the first level, the very moment you spawn. A more recent crashing problem also made me not play as much. The classes have a MOBA style 4 ability set. 1 of these are a normal attack like firing a gun or melee attack. The others have various things such as invulnerability, stronger attacks, nearly unseeable attacks due to their speed, or maybe even all 3.But anyways, the game revolves around you surviving a planet you have crashed onto after an unknown humanoid creature destroys your transport ship. You must go through 6 areas, but to get to the next one, you must activate a teleporter, where you must survive for 90-120 seconds (depending on difficulty) until it is fully operational, and you proceed to finish off the enemies remaining. With time, the game grows more difficult, with enemies gaining more health, damage and also having increased spawn rates (as it seems) and more of the elite mobs appearing. Elite mobs can be approached the same way as the normal type, but you'll most likely get your bum handed to you on a silver platter if you do such a foolish thing. When playing for the first time, there is almost no chance of you beating it. If you do so, congratulations, this game is not going to be difficult for you. This game is fun in a Binding of Isaac way where you never know what you'll get. Gameplay usually is fun and intense, but after a while, the adrenaline stops pumping when you know you'll win, and it just gets a bit boring. Items you unlock with a slight bit of lore behind them in a way, in the form of order details. This makes sense, as you're pretty much were an intergalactic mailman in a way.EDIT: As of recently however, I have been having major problems with the game, such as memory wipes, crashes, and the game messing with my sound. It is to the point where I cannot play the game anymore.Doing neither too little nor too much is key to your survival in this game. If you spend too long leveling up, you will end up dealing with difficulty in the next area, due to a difficulty spike and new enemies to deal with. If you go to the teleporter immediately, with nothing but level 2 and 1 item, death will break down the door and slice your head off, which means, you die near instantly, or you just delay it by running, then die.The soundtrack in this game is absolutely amazing, Chris Christodoulou did a great job with the different pieces. The soundtrack is one of the best I have heard in a long time.New survivors are unlocked by completing various feats like killing a certain 3 bosses, or collecting this or that. Multiplayer is fun as hell, however, online can be a pain in the♥♥♥♥♥♥to get working. Usually zoom scale 1x then resetting it to 2x makes it work, but other problems, sorry, can't help you there. If you get frustrated easily, this is not the game for you. If you hate difficulty, this is not for you. And last but not least, if you hate games where you only have a chance to get the items you so DESPERATELY need, this game is NOT for you.And I have only skimmed the surface of the game for the most part. I leave you to figure out the rest and read other reviews.Gameplay: 8/10Graphics: 8/10Music and Sound:9/10Overall: 8.3/10"
