,Recommended,248820,15448507,"Posted: 19 April, 2015",all,zxvasdf,"Chance of precipitation: 100%Out of all the fancy games I've gotten here on steam, this is the most I've played. I'm relatively new to the scene here, and many of my game preferences tend towards the old school pixelated feel. Risk of Rain is my first roguelike game, and I hated it at first. I was getting nowhere in this game!But patience was employed and I acquired a feel. Once I got a new character I was hooked. The strategic value skyrocketed as I struggled then gleefully adapted to the play style of each character. To date, my favorite of the lot is Engineer, though I do enjoy playing the Loader.Perseverance is key, and one eventually strikes a balance between mining the enemies for xp and coinage and getting the hell out of the stage. It gets progressively harder, and can be frustrating with characters who have a limited range, but you eventually come to grips. Then you get a new character and start all over again.The rainy season has never been this good."
