76561197963949028,Not Recommended,248820,15487855,"Posted: 22 April, 2015",all,levgree,"I would not suggest this game at 10$, maybe 5$.  It is, in a basic sense, an inferior version of Rogue Legacy.  The action game dimension is very simple, mostly kiting enemies and smashing your basic abilities whenever they go off cooldown.  The items aren't too balanced, which is not unusual for a game, but a stronger variety of items may have helped avoid the shoehorned gameplay.The enemies are simple, graphics aren't great (your character model has very little detail).  There is not much progression at all, even within a single game.  You level up and I guess it increases some base stats like health and damage (the game doesn't tell you what gained), no new abilities.Of course it's not an awful game, I'd say in the end I'll rate it 5-7/10. Read other reviews for their positive take on it.  But I don't find it very inspireed, compared to other rogue likes out there."
