,Recommended,248820,10779826,"Posted: 24 June, 2014",all,Majorian,"""Solid Gameplay Mechanics. Excellent Replayability. Subtle Story. (Really) Tough Difficulty. Great Value for Money.""Risk of Rain is a platform shooter using a somewhat simplistic, retro-pixel art style with good attention to its tiny animations. In a similar vein to Faster Than Light, Risk of Rain is an unforgiving roguelike which has your character experiencing permadeath should he be overwhelmed in-game (go easy if you're starting out). What sets this game apart from others within the genre is that its difficulty increases the longer you linger around in-game - genuine pressure that can be felt with really tough enemies (sometimes double/triple/gazillions of bosses) spawned in the next map.While unforgiving in difficulty, it is an easy game to get into - it's a simple run-and-gun combined with several abilities to boost your characters' survivability or firepower. The goal with each map is straightforward: find the teleporter, activate it, face a horde of enemies and slay the boss, survive, teleport to the next level.What makes this game interesting: Finding items are essential in this game, they provide the various boosts required to enhance your survivabililty and ability to take down harder enemies. This is where the crux of the game lies - balancing the amount of time you spend on each level scouring for items to enhance your late game capabilities, a constant tension which makes the experience pretty exciting and at times, really tense.The story may seem scant but is actually pretty subtle and has a haunting tone. The strange/wonderful atmosphere of the world in which you crash-land is further enhanced with the great musical score infused with the game. This immersion is a definite plus in my books.About replayability, Risk of Rain never gets old with the randomization of its maps and the various items/characters it has for the player to unlock - catering to a myriad of playstyles and making for amusing mass explosions should the combined effects of various items permit.Overall, a gem for the affordable price tag, particularly with the ongoing summer sale!(P.S. Be ready to die a lot in-game)A-"
