,Recommended,248820,13489105,"Posted: 20 December, 2014",all,Bronin,"I'm too lazy to write a full on review at the moment, but if I were to do so with a whole detail of pros and cons about this game. Which it has both of, but it usually ends up being that if you're patient enough to struggle for a while it WILL be a rewarding game with a huge replay value. Admittedly that replay value does wear off as you start filling up your item and monster logs, but I still feel like OMG a monster log whenever they drop because it just adds that little extra reward for that game. By all means you will not get a monster log every single playthrough but you will most definitely last longer, get more items, unlock more items, kill more enemies and if you don't it really is your fault. This game is not forgiving but it's not supposed to be. It's supposed to be challenging and it is. It's supposed to be a game you want to try over and over again and for the most part it is. A few tweaks to make the times I discussed more rewarding and less of a struggle, like getting rewarded for improving like an MVP type reward or even just tutorials for each class (after you unlock them). Sure people probably aren't gonna watch them 1st time but they will when they want to be good with  a character. That is one thing I've found is that I don't play certain characters because I've mastered other characters and can't be bothered trying to learn a new archetype, but if I was shown a tutorial on how to use that characters to it's strengths and how and when to use it's abilities just so I play them."
