76561198079433720,Recommended,248820,18720230,"Posted: 27 October, 2015",all,Octo Pus Phd,"Risk of Rain is a fantastic game.That could be my review right there, but I should probably elaborate. This game is fantastic for many reasons, chief among them is the gameplay and music. The gameplay is fun and replayable, with 12 characters (all but one need to be unlocked) all offering thier own playstyles and tactics, ranging from charging at the enemies head-on, to kiting a large group around steadily draining its health. And as the game is roguelike it naturally has unlocks and random-generation, providing many hours of replayability. The music is another selling point (although, while the music is generally well regarded by players and reviewers, it is music, and entirely subjective) as it always seems to fit what is going on on the screen.I only have one minor gripe with the game, in that there is no tutorial or any form of explanation about how to play, and as a result I recommend watching a video review or a quick explanation. Don't worry about that spoiling anything as the games story is told almost entirely through a short cutscene when you launch the game and through unlockable items called monster logs.In conclusion Risk of Rain is a fantastic game with great music and gameplay. But little story or explanation."
