76561198041773731,Recommended,248820,13480965,"Posted: 20 December, 2014",all,Rex Dolorum,"So good. Easily one of my favorite games.It's quick to either pick up and play for a small amount of time, as well as playing for an hour or two in one sitting. The unlockable items, characters, artifacts, and achievements paired with the permadeath push you to do even better on that next run.There's a pretty good variety in the enemies and their own individual attacks, and on top of that, once you get into the higher difficulties there are elite enemies with extra bonuses, such as enemies that can teleport or leave a trail of fire on the ground when they walk.It can be brutally hard since the difficulty increases based on how long you've been playing (for example, after playing one game for 30 minutes the enemies will be much stronger than they were when you were playing for 5 minutes) but once you get a feel for a certain class's abilities and skills as well as the items and how they best work for each class, it can get somewhat easier. I've honestly never had more fun being repeatedly killed in a game than I have had with Risk of Rain.To finish it all off, the soundtrack is amazing.I realize that it's not for everyone, but I would definitely rate Risk of Rain a 10/10."
