76561198040405528,Recommended,248820,11739940,"Posted: 16 August, 2014",all,Vigor Mortis,"If you enjoy a challenge, you'll enjoy this game.The difficulty scales with time, the locations of loot chests and the level's ending gate are all randomized, and the end-level boss brings a swarm of extra enemies to fight. Also, when you die, you either restart from the first level or quit out to the menu  - you get one shot. If you want to buy this game, bear in mind that it'll take you some time to get a handle on the finer points like kiting and dealing with different enemy types, and a little longer to unlock more classes. All ten of the classes have different fighting styles that are easy to pick up but tough to master, as well as their own challenges which reward you with powerful items on completion.The game is lovingly presented in a simple pixel-art style, and the soundtrack is spectacular as well - there are unique tracks for every level and boss in the game, and I'd totally recommend grabbing the soundtrack if you're into music like that of Super Meat Boy or The Binding of Isaac. The game also has a STACK of lore for you - each item has its own flavour text, and there are logs for all of the monsters you can kill as well. I've thoroughly enjoyed my time with this game, and if you like a challenge, you will too.It'll break your heart, then it'll break the rest of you."
