,Recommended,248820,9021936,"Posted: 8 February, 2014",all,Goatburgler,"Here's the thing. This game doesn't have much in terms of variety. There's only a handful of bosses, the levels only differ slightly from playthrough to playthrough, and when you reach the final level you're likely to have a very similar collection of items to your last run.What the game does have, however, is 10 playable classes. These classes aren't just slightly adjusted numbers. They totally change the way in which you play the game. You start with the average Commando class, shooting from a distance and using your dash to maintain a gap between you and your enemies, and then you might unlock the Acrid, whose kit revolves around leaving a trail of poison and slapping enemies to deal damage over time. You'll find that each class you unlock is even more inventive than the last, and the game's replayability shoots through the roof as your desire to master each class grows.Play this game."
