76561198028244196,Recommended,248820,9071072,"Posted: 12 February, 2014",all,LiquidTHC,"Excellent game. Features Rogue-Like, side-scrolling 3rd person shooting with minimalist art-style that is quite striking at times.The soundtrack is also incredible and worth purchasing seperately just for listening to on its own.To clarify, in this game you select from one of 10 classes that each have 4 unique skills (you start out with only 1 class available and unlock the rest as you progress through the game) and then proceed on your adventure.The object of every level is to reach the portal, survive the onslaught of enemies and the boss as the portal charges up, and then proceed to the next level. Along the way you can obtain items from chests and other various receptacles - you might not know what items will do at first but some of them can drastically change your playstyle and aide you in unusual, unforeseen ways.The Rogue-like elements come into play in the sense that you only have one life per go and when you die you have to start fresh from the beginning.All-in-all, from the unique artstyle and soundtrack, to the fun of unlocking and testing out new classes and items, as well as completing your Beastiary of the world's various hostile threats and predators; Risk of Rain will provide fans of games such as Rogue Legacy, Spelunky, etc. (but who are also looking for a much more in-depth and satisfying combat system and enjoy the fun of unlocking new classes and items ) with hours of fun!"
