76561198025009994,Recommended,248820,8743053,"Posted: 17 January, 2014",all,stever98,"If you're interested in sticking with a game for a while and learning it in and out, Risk of Rain is the action-platformer-RPG for you. You will die a lot, but with every death comes more mastery of a class, of items you picked up, and of the enemies you learn how to fight.Many games that go for catharsis instead of difficulty tend to have ""the fast enemy,"" ""the slow enemy,"" ""the flying enemy,"" etc., all fairly bland but fun enough to shoot or cut through. In Risk of Rain, every enemy has personality, a different way of attacking, and various ways to approach killing it. Or two of it. Or ten of it. At first it's a bit much, but eventually you figure out a strategy and it starts working. Suddenly, the first and second levels are a breeze, and now you're learning the third level of the game and its unique challenges.Risk of Rain is not a simple game, but it's not overly complex either. This allows it to be difficult in a perfectly fair way -- you have to adapt to the items you acquire, yes, but they're all useful in defeating your foes. The light complexity and randomness combined with the static nature of your class and the maps used let you become engaged with a game that rewards you for being on your guard and keeping an open mind.If -- and ONLY if -- you're willing to be a curious explorer, and are least okay (not necessarily great) at twitch gaming, I heartily recommend Risk of Rain. If you want to just cool off after work, this isn't the game for you."
76561198018054802,Recommended,248820,8743301,"Posted: 17 January, 2014",all,Colin72GJ19,It good
