,Recommended,248820,9056808,"Posted: 11 February, 2014",all,Exaemo,"This is not an easy game, by any means. Does this make it an undesirable experience? Apparently not, if Demon's/Dark Souls and Flappy Bird (yes, really) are any indication. It has a flat cliff face of a learning curve for the first five minutes as you get adjusted to the flow and then becomes a satisfying lethal adventure.It is by no means a 2D side-scroller whose objective is to maximize your score above all else. No, indeed Risk of Rain brings with it a simply presented but peculiar story, a slowly revealed cast of characters with each unique methods of combat and a flora and fauna of mobs and items worth reading about and hunting for. You'll also be running for your dear life more than that last run on sentence.There are many elements of Risk of Rain that might draw you in to play it: the pixelated art graphics, the many many creatures that you will face, the lore of the world you play in (and are inevitably destined to die in as time/difficulty escalates) but possibly the most impressive of them all is the soundtrack. Just give the trailer a look and I would be surprised if that alone didn't pique your interest.5/5 clapburgers"
