76561198043356212,Recommended,248820,8711949,"Posted: 14 January, 2014",all,Dux,"Up until about a week ago I had never heard of Risk of Rain. I saw a couple of my friends playing it constantly and thought I'd check it out. After watching some gameplay I thought it looked pretty fun for an indie game. However, I didn't expect to get sucked into it like I did. At first it's very frustrating. It plays like a platformer but theres a progression system and you can earn or buy passive/active abilities. The difficulty though is decided by time; the longer you take the harder the game gets. So it's hard to figure out if you should rush through the level or stay and farm. Either way it punishes you. Your saving grace and the best part of the game is the items become more available based on completing challenges (just like Binding of Isaac). This is were you get sucked in trying to do the challenges so you can get better items and even other characters. After most of the items are unlocked each run through the game is much more managable and you end up being a badass by the end of the last level. Aside from the gameplay the music is great, the controls are spot on, and the levels are randomly generated (in shape and order) giving you a lot of replayability. For 10 bucks plus 4 player Co-Op this game is an excellent choice!"
