,Recommended,248820,11226570,"Posted: 13 July, 2014",all,Overswarm,"This game has its faults, but they are outshone by how fun a challenge it is.The game starts out fairly tame; it's very easy to pick up and get started with the commando class and you get a feel for AoE, single use abilities, dodging, etc. The game doesn't really begin until you unlock a few extra characters, and then you're able to have a bit more fun.Unfortunately the characters are very distinctly tiered. Some are great, some are okay, some are mediocre. This is good if you want to give yourself another challenge! But if you want variety, you'll have to handicap yourself to get it.The RNG doesn't effect too much in this game; you can definitely have ""better"" buff drops as the game goes on, but the game drops are set up in such a way that it is highly unlikely you'll get a 'useless' collection of drops.The difficulty is fairly tame on the standard difficulty; I'd suggest doing the harder difficulty setting for a better experience... but only after playing lighter settings to unlock things.The game gets harder the longer you play it (which is good), but it also caps out at a specific difficulty level. I found myself near invulnerable at the end boss when it came to fight him due to all the drops I had!All in all the game is fun, but if you're the kind of guy who can't look back a few design flaws and just have to play a weak class because you like their feel... you might be frustrated. If you're the kind of guy that will get a drop that gives you +max health upon killing an enemy and then continually farm enemies that cannot hurt you until you have obscene amounts of health, this game may turn boring for you quick.Otherwise, you'll have fun."
