,Recommended,248820,7778486,"Posted: 26 November, 2013",all,TJBones,"This is a superb indie game and the whole package really makes me feel nostalgic.  The retro styled visuals are fantastic, the gameplay is tight, and the learning curve is perfect.  There's no hand holding here, a quick prompt of the keyboard controls when you start and you're away.  The selling point of this game is perma-death, which appealed to me instantly, but to some it can be a pain. They've cracked this however.  You can select a difficulty before playing, but this also increases in-game.  For me it's already getting quite hellish between the 20-30 minute mark.Risk and reward is handled really well here, and is akin to heading out when there's a 'Risk of Rain' (hur).  Do you spend more time finding upgrades from chests and statues but run the risk of dying?  Or keep going through the portals, but risk missing out on those vital upgrades.  Speaking of upgrades, each that I've found so far is incredibly satisfying and really make a difference to your progress.I've not played this online yet unfortunately.  When I do I'll update this review.tl;dr: A great indie game which harkens back to the no hands held era of gaming."
