,Recommended,248820,8403991,"Posted: 29 December, 2013",all,TheLegitMidgit,"Risk of Rain is a 2d action roguelike platformer. It has a simple aesthetic and on the surface a simple gameplay. But you soon find out how technical the gameplay is, each character in the game requiring a very good understanding of their respective mechanics to efficiently fight off the hoardes of different monsters in the psuedo-random levels. Each level has a few bosses and a ♥♥♥♥♥on of enemies you must beat before using the teleporter to travel to the next level. The game is not nice to beginners at all, you will start a game and have no clue what to do, or why you are doing it. As you start to understand the game is becomes a lot more fun. It goes like this:1. Start level2. Kill monsters3. Get money4. Buy items and drones5. Kill all monsters6. Teleport to next level7. Repeat steps 1-6 for 6 levelsIt is a very simple premise.In my experience the game is best absorbed with co-op. I have friends over often and a mate and I lost a whole night playing this with local co-op, it was very fun, and frustrating... we only beat the game once.The game is not all great however, it feels a little bit lacking in content. It is just very plain seeming. I would have liked to have seen more items and more levels, but it just does not have them. And sometimes the game really feels like it is out to get you, but that is more just a roguelike thing.Overall I recommend the game. Especially if you enjoy the following:• Co-op roguelikes (Including local)• Roguelikes• Simple pixel art• PlatAnd as a note, in my opinion, the game is much better with a controller."
