76561198010276123,Recommended,248820,8325804,"Posted: 26 December, 2013",all,Dirge the Undying,"""Roguelike"" games are always ridiculously hard and Risk of Rain is no exception. With a ton of different items, stages, enemies, and strategies, no playthrough will be the exact same. Unlike most Rogue games though, Risk of Rain has different difficulties, making it playable to everyone of all skill levels as well. Even vets to the genre like myself have needed to play easy at times.On top of all that, there are 10 characters to unlock as well, each with their own four abilities and stats, very similar to MOBA's like League of Legends, Heroes of Newerth, or DotA. So while one character can benefit from attack speed items, it might not be beneficial to find one for a tanky one. And since it has 4-player online and offline coop, abilities and skills can be mixed and matched, changing things as opposed to playing solo (which is possible even on harder difficulties).All in all, If you want a  platformer like Metal Slug or Cave Story or a Roguelike game like Binding of Isaac, give Risk of Rain a try."
