,Recommended,248820,8212445,"Posted: 22 December, 2013",all,gentlegiant1972,"Risk of Rain is an action platformer with rogue-like elements. But this isn't a bad thing. It features randomly generated environments, permanent death, and even sort of emulates the feel of unkown items. It's not immediately apparent what an item does unless you've already used it, and even then, you may still have to go to the item log to be 100% sure. Proboably the most compelling thing about this game is the replayability. It's hard- really hard. You will die lots, but thankfully the randomness means that the game feels fresh everytime. Additonally, all of the different characters (at least the ones I've unlocked so far) don't just feel slightly differentiated, they feel completely unique. They lend themselves to completely different playstyles and item combinations, and it's really rewarding to try and master one of the new characters. Additionally, unocking them (and the different items in the game for that matter) isn't exactly easy, so the process of trying to unlock new characters and items also makes the grind a little bit more meaningful and bearable.Overall, for the price, this game is excellent, and easily capable of providing you with dozens of hours of enjoyment. It also has one of the best soundtracks for an indie game since in recent memory. Overall, I highly recommend this game to anyone looking for a good time killer."
