76561198078077602,Recommended,248820,7906116,"Posted: 3 December, 2013",all,pwnagrafick,"Risk of Rain is one of those few gems in the action roguelike genre that shouldnt go ignored. Its a vast game with over a hundred items both usable and passive (think Binding Of Isaac) and 10 very different and varied classes. As most people who play any kind of roguelike want a difficult game fronted with a randomized playthrough and permadeath to match this game does it masterfully. While each section is aesthetically very similar in respective stages they actual changes to loot locations and level layout are more than enough to give it hefty replayability without feeling all the same. The soundtrack and effects of the game blend oldschool effects with a very exiting new age soundtrack, this is how audio should be done in action games. While the pacing of the game is very fast since difficulty is scaled with time alive it can kind of get in the way at times, but far more often than not the pacing makes this already tense genre even more nervewracking in the best of ways.Gameplay 8.5/10Presentation 7.5/10Sound 9/10Replayability 10/10Overall for the Price 9/10"
