76561198024088472,Recommended,248820,7907852,"Posted: 4 December, 2013",all,Sargent Peanuts,"A surprisingly addicting 2.5D action platformer. But of course you already know that. In general, the game just works. It combines simple concepts/common practices and does it right. Heads up, this is a long reviewGraphics: Simple, but they work. There're no beautiful sunset vistas, and you won't ever find yourself admiring the detail on a pair of glasses you've picked up, but they still look good enough. Enemy design is interesting, and a few enemies are even a bit terrifying (Parents. You'll know them when you see them). How does it run? Well for the most part at a flawless  60 fps on my laptop (i7-2670QM, 8gb RAM, GT 540m) on... Low. Don't mistake that as shody programing and poor optimization (although I believe it could have been better), I keep the settings on low for two reasons. One, at later levels the game becomes rather hectic, with easily over a hundred enemies on the screen at any one time. Two, if you drop below 50 fps, the speed of the game drops very noticably. It makes sense though, it allows people with toasters to still play the game, but the sudden slowdown (which becomes even more noticable at 40 and 30 fps) can be very jarring and can make the game a bit uncomfortable to play.Gameplay: Much like the rest of the game, simple in concept yet it works. As mentioned it is a 2.5D action platformer. You run left and right, can jump and climb up vines/ladders/whatever happens to be there. The controls are simple. left/right arrows to move, space to jump, and the ZXC and V keys for abilites. I personally changed the combat keys to ASDF, it was simply more comfortable on my hand (mileage may vary). There are 10 characters, all of which are unique and play differently (Huntress FTW). You only start out with the commando however, and you may start to find him to be a little tedious after of couple hours. There are 109 items which act along the lines of statistical buffs (more life, %10 chance to do double damage, chance to evade damage). This is one of two weak points of the game, imo. Now. People have mentioned this game being difficult. I see it as difficult in the way that Dark Souls is difficult (put down your pitchforks). There's a a method to succeeding in this game, and unfortunately in this one it isn't player skill. It's time and [REDACTED]. And a bit of luck, the drops can make or break a round. The difficulty does scale up very quickly though, and later on when the difficulty shoots up and bosses start spawning as starndard enemies, a single misstep can result in instant death. Bonus? Co-op multiplayer! Get some friends and go get your ***** kicked!Replayablity: Moderate to very high, depending on your preference. I've put 26 hours into it over a few days so for me personally it is very high. The 3 different difficulties allow even the newest pansies to play on Drizzle difficulty, while people who don't mind getting punished with no chance of having survived in the first place will enjoy Monsoon difficulty. Rainstorm is plenty difficult for me. There are 5 levels with different areas that you might spawn into randomly. On each level the locations of where you spawn at, the item crate/shops/shrines, and the exit teleporter are all randomized, and with each level being surprisingly (and at times, annoyingly) large maps allow for playing on the same map dozens of time. Additionally, the maps have slight variations depending on what character you are playing (I may be mistaken). Once you reach the 4th level and beat the boss, you have the option to return to the first level (which will once again be randomized) and play through again. If at the end of any level the difficulty gets to much (after having beat the 4th area once that playthrough), you can go to the final level at your own discretion.Story/Atmosphere: There is a very minimal story in Risk of Rain. Basically, a strange being crashes up your ship on a very hostile and mysterious world. You land in a drop pod and then have to fight your way to back to another ship while everything tries to kill you. There was also a nuclear war in 2019. The atmosphere is great, however. The areas look good, and the music is fantastic.Overall, a thouroughly enjoyable game that is a combination of The Binding of Isaac and Contra. Many unlockable characters and items with lots of replayability and an awesome soundtrack.Final note: I'd actually like to see a MOBA/DOTA style game based around Risk of Rain. There is so much here that would fit so well in a MOBA style game."
