76561198022272382,Recommended,248820,10947392,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,Usuper King Zant,"Risk of Rain is a 2D, sidescrolling, rogue-like, shoot 'em up utilizing over a hundred items, 8 characters and a wide and varied array of skills and abilities. Combat is fast paced but strategic and every second counts as the difficulty is constantly increasing from the second you start a game. Multiplayer is either online or hotseat. The only downside to hotseat gameplay is that you all share the same game window meaning that your mobility is limited and because of the large amount of info that must be displayed on one screen items and other stats that are normally displayed in one player aren't during hotseat multiplayer. It's manageable but annoying. Other than this one downside, however, the game shines and is a fantastic, relatively cheap experience that has hours of potential gameplay and huge replayability. Highly recommended for single and multiplayer experiences. But beware, as the game's difficulty is extremely high even on the easiest of settings. It will take new players a little while to get used to it. Enjoy."
