,Recommended,248820,8904163,"Posted: 29 January, 2014",all,Hazz 117,"One of the most beautiful Pixel Art games I've ever played. There is a depth to the gameplay that the ""100's of Items"" gimmick suggests but doesn't totally reveal; Items are all unique, interesting, benificial and stackable. Every character is distressingly different; like one character and it'll make changing to another difficult but extremely rewarding.Time is of the essence, but characters move so damn slow, so choosing to spend time on a level can ultimately end up being your downfall, especially if you decide to go back for an item. Also, multiplayer is a nightmare. In this day and age, seemless matchmaking should be a standard, but here you have to go back to the bad old days of servers, port forwarding and so on.Other than that, a great game! 9/10 would Risk Rain Again."
