,Recommended,248820,9014550,"Posted: 7 February, 2014",all,Asreil Memeurr,"I've seen a YouTuber play the beta for Risk of Rain and it looked interesting, then I finally purchased the full game on Steam. Afterwards I enjoyed countless hours of putting lead into all who oppose me.I'm a sucker for class-styled warfare, so I of course had an attachment to the game the very first time I played it, the only negative things I can say is that the fighting and bosses are consistent, you always will have to use the same strategy every time; however I do not know how they can improve or fix this, as this is a problem for most bosses on games of its type. I started playing and I thought the music was pretty good at first, seemed like a casual everyday 8-bit style soundtrack, until I got to the final level, where apparently my emotional side kicked in, along with my adrenaline, it was very confusing. If you're interested in 2-D, 8-bit soundtracks, class warfare and diverse enemies you never thought even devs could imagine, buy this game.An aspect I have yet to decide is cool or lame yet is the unlocking of classes. Yes, that's right, in order to actually GET the classes, you have to unlock them. However it is interesting, and puts a spin on this survival game. It can get a bit boring somewhat far in, but that can be stopped by going to the next level. With each level you advance to, a whole new slew of enemies comes along with it, and with that comes new strategies to killing them. Some enemies require no strategy, as they are either too fast or attack so accurately that you cannot possibly counter it, or are so easily defeated you need not waste time on making a plan to killing them. I must say the final difficulty level is frightening, but as of the current version and date (2/7/14) it doesn't come with any massive boss mob that wants to tear out your flesh, disappointingly.In conclusion I will give Risk of Rain an 8/10, seeing as I have invested so much time dedicated to defeating the final boss, but I have also been repeating myself for at least half an hour on just the final fight. All in all, its a good game."
