,Recommended,248820,11648130,"Posted: 10 August, 2014",all,Darples,"This game... is amazing.First off, this game is 100 megabites, yet you can get alot of playtime out of it. You got 10 Classes to unlock, over 100 items to get, and 9 artifacts that can modify your play experience. Without artifacts, you have the vanilla Risk of Rain: Kill stuff, get money to get random items, find a teleporter and murder a boss. And yes, this game is hard at first. Theres the challenge for you, but after you start unlocking things the game gets more fun and interesting. The replayability is off the charts for this game! Ive unlocked 8 artifacts and all 10 classes, still havent found a favorite. There are 6 ranged classes and 4 melee classes, with each class having a 4 ability kit with the 1st ability being their ""Basic attack"" and their 4th being their ""Ultimate"" (You can get an ancient scepter which upgrades it, just like in dota 2, its awesome lol) You level up but that just increases your health and damage. You start off as the commando class which is not the strongest but is well rounded. Heres a brief run down of the classes in order:1: Commando(Ranged)Shoots and rolls and shoots and pierces and rolls and dies. Can last very long if played right.2: Enforcer(Close Ranged)Uses a shotgun and can block damage while stunning groups of enemies. Tank.3: Bandit(Ranged)Uses a rifle, can  stealth and can reset cooldowns with his ult if it kills the enemy, not very mobile though.4: Huntress(Ranged)VERY good at kiting. Her mechanics let her shoot things with her bow while moving the opposite way.5: HAN-D(Melee)CC FOR DAYS! Hes a robot that punches and hammer-slams. I built him tanky with attack speed and rekt!6: Engineer(Close Range)Shoots useless grenades. Just place his turrets then fire his harpoons and watch everything die :)7: Miner-(Melee)He's short and stout, and definitely not a teacup! Dual wields pickaxes and can launch himself into the air.8: Sniper-(Ranged)Uses a rifle, can 1 hit bosses, however, like gears of war, you have to reload and try to get it perfectly.9: Acrid-(Melee)Swipes and chomps, which in turn stacks poison. He does ALOT of damage over time!10: Mercenary-(Melee)Uses a laser sword and is kinda like Megaman Z, he can dash around and use an omnislash (dota 2 ref)There are 9 wonderful stages in this game that you go to randomly and spawn in random parts of. Each stage except for the final one has a 2nd variant. You will want to play in both variants of the stages if you want to unlock artifacts and classes. The one downside I had with this game was I started to get bored after consecutive fails at trying to unlock things. I wanted the command artifact, which rather than getting random items you get a box with items of that rarity that you can pick, which lets you build items rather than take what you're given. I had issues constantly getting the wrong map variant, but I eventually got it and all was good.This game actually has an interesting plot. Nothing to spoil, just material. The final boss of Risk of Rain is a mysterious figure named Providence. He teleports on to the players transport ship and explodes it which sends the player and various chests flying to the planet below. The player then must survive and defeat enemies in order to use the teleporters that he finds to somehow get back on to the ship. Once the player gets back on the ship, presumably leveled up and geared, the player must make its way to the bridge and leave the planet, however Providence shows up again and attacks you. The player then has a long battle with Providence and his 2 pet wurms and defeats him, and then leaves the planet. Each class has a different ending which is nice. What makes this game interesting is the monster logs. You need to get 15 of them to unlock the huntress, but Providence's log brings more into the story. The player seems to regret killing Providence, feeling like some mistake was made, wondering why the teleporter was on the ship in the first place. This could make way for more story in this game later! Like Providence was somehow protecting everyone from something and the player set in motion something bad. I don't know but its well done!And to wrap this up, this game is well worth $10. But here is what ASTONISHED me. I've been practicing using this scripting software known as game maker, i've been using the older version called Game Maker 8, after a while of playing this game I started to think, hey maybe this game was made with game maker? And out of pure curiousity I look at Hopoo's blog.THIS GAME WAS MADE BY 3 GUYS IN COLLEGE WITH GAME MAKER 8 LOL!   I was so amazed, I've made a few games in game maker 8, but this game tops it all, and only 100 megabites for the hours you get out of this. And anything can run this game so its really, just amazing to me. Thanks for caring to read this review, DEFINITELY GET THIS GAME!"
,Recommended,248820,10938564,"Posted: 29 June, 2014",all,[Zeu5]Uzi790,"This game is great. I highly recommend it.The game is highly replayable. 10 very unique classes each have their own playstyles, and getting good at everyone will take a while. however, some classes are more/less useful than the others.  For instance. The huntress is currently ""the best"" class because she is the only one who can attack and move simultaneously. and the sniper, who's good on paper, but struggles compared to everyone else.the graphics are decent, but nothing to shout about.The random aspect of the game keeps everything interesting and stops it getting repetitive. The game isn't truly random, but it's random enough to stop it becoming a guessing game, while still keeping everything fresh. The large amount of items, each of which unique, are also randomly obtained, so it makes each item memorable. Like one making all your attacks explode, and one making time stop for a couple of seconds when you're close to dying. The artifact system they also added adds more to the game, making it easier, harder, or less random. It's mostly for hardcore players who've played a ton of the game.Plot:VERY little plot. Of what there is, it's ""you are stuck on this planet, Survive and get out"". And then there's the idea of you actually being the bad guy. No more because spoilers. Lore can be obtained through monster logs which randomly drop from enemies rarely. and through the ""item logs"". that you get when picking up new items.Soundtrack: Very good, the soundtrack is actually within the steam folder so if you buy it you can listen to it!Multiplayer: I've hardly played multiplayer, but from what i've heard, it works, but doesn't work well. With some supposedly bad netcode and lots of bugs. But don't let that deter you. The game is a ton of fun with friendsComplaints: The final teleporter has two options. Go to first level, or go to final level. hard to explain, but the way you choose this really bugs me. Just a minor thing. Some people report very bad performance in this game, despite having great rigs. some characters less useful. Some achievements are ridiculous, like reaching the 3rd teleporter without taking damage.Conclusion: This game is great. there's a demo out there you can try if you want. If you have lots of friends to play with, it is more fun. It's worth the price, even more so on a sale."
