,Recommended,248820,8724221,"Posted: 15 January, 2014",all,Paradigmical,"This game is the FTL of 2013. It has a random element that can sometimes doom you and sometimes be your best friend, but there is rarely any time I do anything and don't think it's my own fault. That said, the game has a pretty sharp difficulty curve; you don't know what any items are until the first time you use them, at which point they get added to a database/archive, and each character's abilities come from a MOBA-ish list where each has its own cooldown, and the strategy and delicate balance of timing behind the skills takes a bit of time to learn. In addition to this, the game is not without its issues. It requires Hamachi to play online, there are often bugs with enemies walking into corners then just refusing to move any more, and I have lost audio before.All in all, this game is a pretty difficult roguelike action 2D-shooter with mild platforming elements and a certain degree of randomness that never feels unfair or cheap, and will sink its talons into you and any friends you invite to try it out."
