,Recommended,248820,12507270,"Posted: 15 October, 2014",all,thetwistedkris,This game feels so unique and the only way I can describe it is an action platormer with rogue-like and MOBA elements. Definitely a must play-to-hell and a time sink where all your time is well spent.
76561198049724851,Recommended,248820,12514194,"Posted: 16 October, 2014",all,Fenris,"Risk of Rain is a game that doesn't ease you into things. you're into the thick of it, right away. No tutorials, no long intro, nada. This is both its greatest strength and its biggest weakness. It makes it insanely replayable, but it also makes it difficult to get into initially. The starting class is very well balanced, but to the point that it becomes a jack of all trades. It does well at everything, but doesnt excell at any particular one either. This is not really a weakness, however, as it introduces a multitude of different playstyles. The biggest strength of the game comes from its replayability. I personally have gotten to the point where I almost never lose on normal difficulty. This means that I go to the very end and beat the final boss almost every game I play. And for those who play this game and know what this is; I don't use boar beach. And yet, even with this being the case, I still have a very high amount of replayability. The highest difficulty is on an entirely different level to the normal difficulty, and thats not a bad thing. It prevents the game from getting stale, as the reason it is replayable is that it always provides a higher challenge for you. You beat the game with your favorite class? Alright, try a harder difficulty, or a different class. The game is only over once you say it is, and it provides enough variety that its pretty difficult to put down. All in all, its a wonderful little game, with a beautiful soundtrack. I thoroughly recommend it to anyone who enjoys challenging games, and I still encourage others to try it out as well. It wont be your favorite game of all time, but it may very well keep you going after it longer than your favorite game."
