,Recommended,248820,12599955,"Posted: 21 October, 2014",all,Vastonik,"I honestly had a lot of fun with this game. I started playing the game not really thinking much of it and was just getting hang of the controls. I must say, after I unlocked a couple items I got hooked and was determined to 100% the game.Unlocking characters and items has to be one of the most exciting things about this game. Completing challenges for characters and new items is a lot of fun and keeps the replayability aspect of the game rolling and rolling.My only downside of the game is the multiplayer. No matter how good the connection is between two or more people, the game is extremely buggy, laggy, and has broken enemies that are invincible or non-existant preventing the other player from progressing and forcing a restart.Other than the horrid-netcode, the game is amazing, and I'm still going to give it an 8/10 because multiplayer is not an intended main focus of the game.P.S I'm very happy they're still adding content to the game. I'll probably play for another 10 hours when the next patch comes out."
